<F P=100> ARAB PENINSULA </F>
<F P=101> Yemen </F>
<H3> <TI>   Sanaa Radio Defends `Tolerance' of Armed Forces </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Sanaa Radio Defends `Tolerance' of Armed Forces </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN1405135094 Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network in Arabic 
1241 GMT 14 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN1405135094 </F>
<F P=104>  Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed commentary] </F>
  [Text] O sons of our great people in beloved Aden, in 
(?the plains of) al-Hawtah, in the villages and [words 
indistinct], and in all areas of Yemen: The rumors circulated 
by the trumpeting dwarfs of the gang of apostasy and secession 
about your Armed Forces, the forces of unity and legitimacy, are 
stained with a sense of aggressive and regional bias that 
reflects the structure of that gang. They have been violating 
the will of the people and their values throughout the era in 
which they were in control. They, as well our people, realize 
the extent of the tolerance, brotherhood, and generosity 
displayed by the forces of unity and legitimacy toward the 
deceived ones who directed their weapons against unity and 
legitimacy. 
  Can our people believe these degenerate rumors after seeing 
with their own eyes the tolerance of the leader president in 
'Imran and the tolerance of our forces, the forces of unity, in 
al-Dali', Musaymir, Mukayras, Abyan, and (?Rassal). 
  With all honesty and sincerity, we stress that the forces of 
unity and legitimacy view as equal all citizens of Yemen. They 
have always been, and will remain, the protectors of the 
citizens and their property and honor, and the protectors of the 
people's sacred goal in defending unity and Constitutional 
legitimacy. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

