<F P=100> IRAQ </F>
<H3> <TI>   Tariq 'Aziz Meets With Figures at UN in New York </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Tariq 'Aziz Meets With Figures at UN in New York </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Meets Supporters of Lifting Sanctions </H4>

<F P=102> JN1605121094 Baghdad Republic of Iraq Radio Network in 
Arabic 1030 GMT 15 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN1605121094 </F>
<F P=104>  Baghdad Republic of Iraq Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] At the Iraqi Mission in New York yesterday, 
Deputy Prime Minister Tariq 'Aziz received a delegation of Arab 
and international figures participating in an international 
campaign against the unjust blockade imposed on Iraq. 
  During a reception held by the Iraqi Mission in the honor of 
the figures, the deputy prime minister reviewed Iraq's position, 
which sees the need for the Security Council to recognize the 
facts that are supported by UN circles in charge of implementing 
UN resolutions. 
  Tariq 'Aziz said Iraq has implemented a great deal of these 
resolutions, and it is now the turn of the Security Council to 
recognize these facts and consequently lift the unjust blockade 
imposed on Iraq. 
  The deputy prime minister said one member only; namely, the 
United States, is using its influence to prevent the 
implementation of Security Council resolutions. It thus 
represents the minority at the Security Council. 
  Tariq 'Aziz answered questions by several members of the 
delegation of international personalities on Iraq's relationship 
with the Security Council. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

