<F P=100> IRAQ </F>
<H3> <TI>   Tariq 'Aziz Meets With Figures at UN in New York </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Tariq 'Aziz Meets With Figures at UN in New York </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Meets Security Council Nonaligned Envoys </H4>

<F P=102> JN1605185494 Baghdad Republic of Iraq Radio Network in 
Arabic 1800 GMT 16 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN1605185494 </F>
<F P=104>  Baghdad Republic of Iraq Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Deputy Prime Minister Tariq 'Aziz met at the United 
Nations today with the ambassadors of the UN Security Council 
nonaligned member states. 
  The deputy prime minister briefed the Nonaligned Movement's 
ambassadors on Iraq's stand on the implementation of pertinent 
UN Security Council resolutions. 
  In a brief press statement, Tariq 'Aziz expressed 
satisfaction with the results of this meeting. He told 
journalists that the meeting was "characterized by a spirit of 
friendship." 
  Taking part in the meeting were the ambassadors of Oman, 
Djibouti, Nigeria, Rwanda, and Pakistan--nonpermanent members of 
the UN Security Council. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

