<F P=100> Tunisia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Foreign Minister Ben Yahya Meets Jordanian Minister </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Foreign Minister Ben Yahya Meets Jordanian Minister </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1605185594 Tunis Tunisian Republic Radio Network in Arabic 
1700 GMT 16 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1605185594 </F>
<F P=104>  Tunis Tunisian Republic Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpts] Foreign Minister Habib Ben Yahya had talks today 
with Mr. Talal Sat'an al-Hasan, Jordanian minister of state for 
foreign affairs. [passage omitted] 
  Following the meeting, Mr. Talal Sat'an al-Hasan made a 
statement to Tunis-Afrique Press Agency in which he pointed out 
that his visit to Tunisia had been within the framework of 
consultations and coordination between the two countries to 
bolster their bilateral cooperation in all spheres. 
  The Jordanian foreign minister added that the talks had 
dealt 
with a number of political issues, particularly those revolving 
around Jordan's efforts to give momentum to the Middle East 
peace process to allow the Palestinian people to exercise their 
legitime rights. 
  He indicated, furthermore, that the two sides had examined 
the means for bolstering political coordination between the two 
countries and for finding the suitable mechanism for making such 
coordiantion more successful and more effective and achieving 
the best possible results out of it. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

