<F P=100> ISRAEL </F>
<H3> <TI>   Two Dead, 1 Wounded in Hebron `Terrorist' Attack </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Two Dead, 1 Wounded in Hebron `Terrorist' Attack </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Hamas Claims Responsibility </H4>

<F P=102> TA1705083494 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 0800 GMT 17 
May 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA1705083494 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] [passage omitted] In a telephone call to Qol 
Yisra'el's Arabic-language Department, the Hamas [Islamic 
Resistance Movement] 'Izz-al-Din al-Qassam terrorist squad 
claimed responsibility for this morning's attack near Hebron. 
The callers gave details about the way the attack was 
perpetrated. Army forces, headed by Major General Sha'ul Mufaz, 
IDF [Israel Defense Forces] commander in Judaea and Samaria, 
were rushed to the scene of the attack. Our correspondent Moti 
Amir reports that the vehicle in which the terrorists were 
traveling was found totally burned a short time ago in Hebron. 
  Deputy Defense Minister Mordekhay Gur said that extremists 
in 
the Palestinian camp want to torpedo the peace process but will 
have no choice but to enter into negotiations with us. Gur sent 
condolences to the families of the dead and wished the wounded 
woman a speedy recovery. The deputy minister is touring Israeli 
settlements in the Jericho area today. He passed through 
Jericho but did not stop there. 
  Reactions in the Knesset to the attack: The National 
Religious Party said this is merely the opening shot in a joint 
offensive by the PLO and the other terrorist organizations. 
Tzomet said it is additional proof that the actions of the 
Palestinians will force us into a bloody war. Our correspondent 
Hayim Hecht reports that Moledet said today's deaths are more on 
the list of Yitzhaq Rabin's war casualties. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

