<F P=100> ISRAEL </F>
<H3> <TI>   11 Arabs Injured in Clash With Settlers, IDF </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    11 Arabs Injured in Clash With Settlers, IDF </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA1605162194 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 1600 GMT 16 
May 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA1605162194 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] In Hebron, 11 residents were wounded in incidents 
this afternoon. A group of settlers was pelted with rocks, and 
one of them opened fire. Our correspondent Moti Amir reports 
that, according to various reports, three Palestinian residents 
were apparently injured by the shooting. Another eight were 
injured when the IDF [Israel Defense Forces] moved in to put out 
riots which followed the shooting incident in Hebron. One of 
the wounded is in grave condition, two suffer medium wounds, and 
the rest were lightly wounded. 
  Representatives of the Temporary International Presence in 
Hebron arrived at the site of the incident and began collecting 
evidence from the Arab residents of Hebron. The Jews did not 
testify about the incident. Also, the IDF has not yet detained 
any settler for questioning, but an IDF unit is on its way to 
the Shavey Hevron Yeshiva to investigate which of the settlers 
fired the shots. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS4-59701 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drnes095_l_94006" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-NES-94-095 </AU>
Daily Report 
<DATE1>  16 May 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> ISRAEL </F>
<H3> <TI>   Further on Incident </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Further on Incident </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA1605193094 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 1900 GMT 16 
May 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA1605193094 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The security forces are investigating the incident 
in which 19 Arab residents and three border policemen were 
injured in Hebron this afternoon. The incident started when 
Jewish residents were walking through Policeman's Square in town 
and came under a hail of rocks. They shot at the stone 
throwers, wounding nine Arabs. IDF [Israel Defense Forces] 
patrols that arrived at the site were also pelted with rocks. 
They were forced to shoot in an attempt to disperse the stone 
throwers, and apparently wounded 10 residents. The IDF detained 
two yeshiva students from the region for questioning about the 
shooting. The city of Hebron was declared closed military zone. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

