<F P=100> ISRAEL </F>
<H3> <TI>   IDF Shoots 2 Palestinians in Gaza Firefight </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    IDF Shoots 2 Palestinians in Gaza Firefight </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA1505154294 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in English 1500 GMT 15 
May 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA1505154294 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] In the Gaza Strip, Israeli soldiers shot and 
wounded two Palestinians who opened fire on them from a truck 
near the settlement Morag. There were no Israeli casualties. 
Our reporter Alan Ben-'Ami says the gunmen got away and a joint 
Israeli-Palestinian team arrived on the scene to investigate. 
  Meanwhile, the Israeli pullout from Gaza is nearly complete. 
The Civil Administration building was turned over to the 
Palestinians this afternoon at a ceremony attended by Brigadier 
General David Gazit, Israel's head of the Civil Administration 
in the strip. Four hundred more Palestinian policemen are due 
to arrive in the Gaza Strip from Egypt today. 

</TEXT>

