<F P=100> ISRAEL </F>
<H3> <TI>   PLO Receives More Gaza Government Offices </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    PLO Receives More Gaza Government Offices </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA1605135494 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 1300 GMT 16 
May 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA1605135494 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] As part of the transfer of Civil Administration 
powers to the PLO in Gaza, the Palestinians received today the 
center of control over government offices in Gaza Strip and 
independent apparatuses which serve, among other things, the 
Interior and Agriculture Ministries. 
  The commander of the computer unit, Major Yoram Baraq, 
believes that unless they are helped by Israel, the Palestinians 
will have many problems operating the systems, although during 
the overlap period they have acquired a reasonable basis to 
begin working. 
  Our correspondent Karmela Menashe notes that the IDF [Israel 
Defense Forces] has, in fact, evacuated the entire Gaza Strip, 
except for the brigade headquarters, the governor's house, and 
several other small installments. The ceremony of handing 
control of the Gaza Strip over to the Palestinians is due to 
take place tomorrow at the Qatif Bloc. 
  Brigadier General Dubi Gazit, Head of the Civil 
Administration in the Gaza Strip, said after the PLO accept the 
authority there is no reason they would not to be able to manage 
the administration themselves. If any problems should occur, 
they would be discussed by the regional committee on civilian 
affairs, he said. 

</TEXT>

