<H3> <TI>   Labor Decides To Pass Histadrut in `Orderly' Way </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Labor Decides To Pass Histadrut in `Orderly' Way </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA1505092594 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 0900 GMT 15 
May 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA1505092594 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Labor ministers today decided to pass control of 
the Histadrut labor federation to Ramon's list in an orderly and 
dignified way. Contacts on this issue will commence on Tuesday 
[17 May]. In a meeting of Labor ministers today, Prime Minister 
Rabin said the transfer of power must be completed quickly in 
order to prevent a feeling of procrastination. Our party 
affairs correspondent Shmu'el Tal reports that Minister Liba'i 
proposed to remove Hayim Haberfeld and Nisim Zvili from the 
negotiations team. Minister Qeysar reacted angrily to this 
proposal. Minister Ora Namir also said that Haberfeld should 
not conduct these negotiations. Minister Ben-Eli'ezer said the 
elections proved that the age of ideology is over, and the only 
thing which remains now is the media. Foreign Minister Peres 
said the elections do not merely constitute a defeat for the 
Labor Party, but also signal the end of the Histadrut. 

</TEXT>

