<H3> <TI>   Mauritanian Prime Minister Concludes Visit </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Mauritanian Prime Minister Concludes Visit </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1605132094 Rabat MAP in English 1259 GMT 16 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1605132094 </F>
<F P=104>  Rabat MAP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Rabat, May 16 (MAP) -- Mauritanian Prime Minister 
Sidi Mohamed Ould Boubaker left Morocco over the week-end after 
a several day visit during which he conveyed a message to King 
Hassan II from President Maaouiya Ould Sid'Ahmed Taya. 
  In a departure statement, the Mauritanian premier voiced 
satisfaction over the outcome of his visit to Morocco and hailed 
the sound cooperation and secular ties binding the two countries. 
  During his stay, Ould Boubaker conferred with Moroccan peer 
Mohamed Karim Lamrani on ways of boosting bilateral cooperation 
in all fields. The two sides agreed to convene next June in 
Rabat a meeting of the follow-up cooperation commission to 
prepare the agenda of the high joint commission in charge of 
economic, technical and cultural cooperation. 

</TEXT>

