<F P=100> SYRIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Christopher Meets al-Shar', Leaves Damascus </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Christopher Meets al-Shar', Leaves Damascus </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN1605164294 Damascus Syrian Arab Republic Radio Network in 
Arabic 1515 GMT 16 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN1605164294 </F>
<F P=104>  Damascus Syrian Arab Republic Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Damascus -- At the request of the U.S. side, a 
session of talks was held between Foreign Minister Faruq 
al-Shar' and U.S. Secretary of State Warren Christopher at the 
Foreign Ministry this morning. The talks were attended by Walid 
al-Mu'allim, Syrian ambassador in Washington, and Dennis Ross, 
U.S. coordinator of the Middle East peace process. 
  During this session, the two sides continued the discussion 
of the ideas and proposals that were dealt with by His 
Excellency President Hafiz al-Asad and Christopher yesterday. 
  U.S. Secretary of State Warren Christopher and the 
delegation 
accompanying him left Damascus at 1600 today at the end of a 
two-day visit to Syria. 
  He was seen off at Damascus International Airport by Foreign 
Minister Faruq al-Shar', the Syrian ambassador in Washington, 
and the U.S. ambassador in Damascus. 

</TEXT>

