<F P=100> SOUTH ASIA </F>
<F P=101> Iran </F>
<H3> <TI>   Red Crescent's Aid to Bosnia Tallied </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Red Crescent's Aid to Bosnia Tallied </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1605121694 Tehran IRNA in English 1140 GMT 16 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1605121694 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran IRNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tehran, May 16, IRNA -- Iran's Red Crescent Society 
(IRCS) has so far sent some 5,000 tons of relief supplies 
including foodstuff and clothings to Bosnia-Herzegovina since 
the start of Serbian aggression against Bosnian Muslims, 
reported the IRCS's public relations department today. 
  The relief supplies, shipped aboard seven airplanes, 25 
trucks and a cargo ship, have been sent to the war stricken 
Bosnian Muslims, the report said. 
  In order to avoid high transportation costs, the IRCS has 
also purchased relief supplies worth about dlrs 250,000 from 
Bosnia's neighboring countries and has distributed them among 
Bosnian Muslims, it said. 
  The IRCS's relief operation in Bosnia-Herzegovina is 
coordinated by four of its branches, three of which are located 
in Zagreb, Sarajevo and Slovenia. 

</TEXT>

