<H3> <TI>   Hajj Rally for Deliverance Set for 17 May </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Hajj Rally for Deliverance Set for 17 May </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1405205994 Tehran IRNA in English 2037 GMT 14 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1405205994 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran IRNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Mecca, May 14, IRNA -- Hojjat ol-Eslam Mohammad 
Mohammadi Reyshahri, the representative of the leader of the 
Islamic revolution for the annual hajj ceremony said here today 
that the rally for deliverance from disbelievers, will be held 
on Tuesday [17 May] in front of the leader's bureau in holy 
Mecca. 
  The hojjat ol-eslam who was talking to the leaders of 
caravans and Iranian pilgrims in Mecca asked them to participate 
in the rally like previous years. 
  He quoted the father of the Islamic revolution, the imam 
Khomeyni, as having said that participating in this rally was 
necessary. 
  Reyshahri added that participants must observe peace and 
discipline in this rally, which is aimed at fostering Islamic 
unity and enlightening the ummah on the dangers besetting them 
from the disbelievers. 
  He observed that God willing the rally will go ahead as 
planned without any untoward incident. 

</TEXT>

