<H3> <TI>   Majles Speaker Regrets Cancellation </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Majles Speaker Regrets Cancellation </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1705100494 Tehran IRNA in English 0952 GMT 17 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1705100494 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran IRNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tehran, May 17, IRNA -- Majles Speaker 'Ali Akbar 
Nateq-Nuri here Tuesday expressed regret over the measures taken 
by Saudi rulers to prevent the "Disavowal of Pagans" ceremony by 
Hajj pilgrims in Mecca. 
  Since the ceremony threatens the interests of the global 
arrogance and its allies, the Saudi rulers prevented the Iranian 
pilgrims and those from other countries from holding the 
ceremony, said the speaker at the open session of Majles. Such 
actions were not unexpected from Saudi rulers in order to serve 
the interests of the enemies of Islam, he said adding that 
fortunately they were thwarted by the awareness of the leader's 
representative for Hajj-related affairs, Mohammad 
Mohammadi-Reyshahri. 
  The speaker then described today's silence of Hajj pilgrims 
as very meaningful and added that this would exopose the real 
nature of the Saudi rulers for the Muslims world over. 

</TEXT>

