<H3> <TI>   Visit of Kazakhstani Prime Minister Reported </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Visit of Kazakhstani Prime Minister Reported </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Tereshchenko, Habibi Meet </H4>

<F P=102> LD1405095294 Tehran IRNA in English 0929 GMT 14 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1405095294 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran IRNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tehran, May 14, IRNA -- The visiting Kazakh Prime 
Minister Sergey Tereshchenko and Vice-President Hassan Habibi 
here Saturday described Tehran-Almaty relations as friendly and 
growing since Kazakhstan's independence. 
  The Kazakh official said that the objective of his three-day 
official visit to Tehran is to remove the obstacles in the way 
of promotion of bilateral ties. 
  He expressed hope that mutual cooperation in industial and 
agricultural fields as well as in air and marine transport would 
further expand and letters of understanding be signed in the 
said areas. 
  The Kazakh premier noted that establishment of the joint 
chambers of commerce and exchange of views on bilateral trade 
will be among other topics he will discuss with Iranian 
officials. 
  In reply Habibi said that said that grounds had been 
provided 
for the expansion of Tehran-Almaty economic, social and cultural 
relations in exchange of visits between President Akbar Hashemi 
Rafsanjani and his Kazakh counterpart Nursultan Nazarbayev in 
Tehran. 
  He said that a number of agreements had also been inked by 
the two sides, adding that during its stay here the Kazakh 
delegation can pave the way for implmentation of the said 
agreements. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

