<H3> <TI>   Khamene'i Meets Chancellor of Islamic Open University </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Khamene'i Meets Chancellor of Islamic Open University </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1605111094 Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network in Persian 0930 GMT 16 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1605111094 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network </F>

<F P=105>  Persian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpts] The esteemed leader of the Islamic revolution, 
His Eminence Ayatollah Khamene'i, has met the chancellor and 
deputy heads of the Islamic Open University [IAU] and the heads 
of this university's branches from all over the country. He 
made a speech praising the role played by the IAU in providing 
higher education in every region of the country. The esteemed 
leader stressed the need for maintaining the religious and 
revolutionary atmosphere ruling over the IAU. 
  During the meeting the esteemed leader welcomed the future 
IAU plans to upgrade the academic achievements of this 
university and to promote full supremacy of Islamic values. He 
said: The IAU atmosphere must be protected from the penetration 
of poisonous and anti-Islamic thoughts, and the managing board 
of this private university is justified in preventing the 
expression of any remarks against the Islamic and revolutionary 
values in the teaching and research environment. [passage 
omitted] 
  The esteemed leader of the Islamic revolution referred to 
the 
strong religious and revolutionary belief of the people as the 
main factor enabling them to stand against the all-round 
pressures of the enemies of Islam. 
  In conclusion, His Eminence Ayatollah Khamene'i stressed 
that 
the IAU graduates, who are blessed with Islamic ethics, will be 
accepted and relied upon in all departments of the regime. 
[passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

