<H3> <TI>   Buwayz Returns From Pretoria, Views Christopher Trip </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Buwayz Returns From Pretoria, Views Christopher Trip </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC1605201594 Beirut Radio Lebanon in Arabic 1900 GMT 16 May 
94 </F>

<F P=103> NC1605201594 </F>
<F P=104>  Beirut Radio Lebanon </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpts] This evening Foreign Minister Faris Buwayz 
returned to Beirut from South Africa where he was attending the 
inauguration of President Nelson Mandela. In his arrival 
statement, Buwayz said his participation in Mandela's 
inauguration reflects Lebanon's support for the return of 
democracy and genuine representation in South Africa. Here is a 
recording of Minister Buwayz' statement to colleague Darwish 
'Ammar: 
  [Begin recording] [passage omitted] ['Ammar] Mr. Minister, 
it 
is known that U.S. Secretary of State Warren Christopher began a 
new tour of the region. Do you know if he will visit Lebanon? 
What does Lebanon expect from Christopher's tour? 
  [Buwayz] So far, we have not been informed of a possible 
visit to Lebanon by Christopher. We do not expect such a visit. 
I believe that Secretary Christopher is trying to address 
problems related to the Syrian-Israeli track of negotiations. 
As far as I know, his proposals are still somewhat far from 
constituting a genuine and constructive common ground. [end 
recording] 

</TEXT>

