<F P=100> ARABIAN PENINSULA </F>
<F P=101> Qatar </F>
<H3> <TI>   Yemen's Basindwah Holds Talks With Amir, Officials </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Yemen's Basindwah Holds Talks With Amir, Officials </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Basindwah Sets Conditions for Cease-Fire </H4>

<F P=102> JN1805142494 Manama WAKH in Arabic 1320 GMT 18 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> JN1805142494 </F>
<F P=104>  Manama WAKH </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Doha, 18 May (WAKH)--Yemeni Foreign Minister 
Muhammad Salim Basindwah has set four conditions for beginning a 
cease-fire, namely, recognizing legitimacy and the Constitution, 
resorting to the Constitution, the merger of the Armed Forces' 
units, and the surrender of the southern leaders to the 
legitimate leadership. 
  At a news conference he gave in Doha today at the end of his 
visit to the State of Qatar, the Yemeni minister said that the 
southern leaders' failure to meet these conditions will mean 
their inevitable end. 
  He asserted that secession is impossible, pointing out that 
Yemen will never again return to partition. 
  He added that what is happening is that the Yemeni 
leadership 
is defending legitimacy and the Constitution, adding that the 
legitimate leadership is eager to end the bloodshed, but that 
fighting has been imposed on it. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

