<F P=101> Yemen </F>
<H3> <TI>   Prime Minister al-'Attas Talks With U.S. Official </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Prime Minister al-'Attas Talks With U.S. Official </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   EA1805092094 Aden Yemeni Republic Radio Network in Arabic 
0330 GMT 18 May 1994 </F>

<F P=103> EA1805092094 </F>
<F P=104>  Aden Yemeni Republic Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Council of Ministers Chairman Haydar Abu-Bakr 
al-'Attas met Mr. Pelletreau, the Assistant State Secretary for 
Near East Affairs at the U.S. State Department yesterday. They 
discussed the grave developments in our country and the 
continued barbaric attacks led by the military leadership in 
control in Sanaa against the people of the southern and eastern 
provinces. 
  Prime Minister al-'Attas reviewed the peace initiative 
proposed by the Yemeni Socialist Party and the principles for 
national salvation accord proposed by the nationalist forces 
which were both rejected along with other political initiatives 
by the leadership in Sanaa. 
  The U.S. official expressed the U.S. Administration's 
satisfaction with and welcome of this initiative stressing his 
country's keen interest in stopping the war. He pointed out 
that whatever the result of the war is, it cannot be a solution 
to the current political problems. It will rather lead to more 
ruin, destruction, and victims and will create hatred and 
bitterness and expose the union to danger. 

</TEXT>

