<H3> <TI>   Al-Bid Begins Military Inspection Tour in East </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Al-Bid Begins Military Inspection Tour in East </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   EA1705222594 Aden Yemeni Republic Radio Network in Arabic 
1900 GMT 17 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> EA1705222594 </F>
<F P=104>  Aden Yemeni Republic Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Brother 'Ali Salim al-Bid, vice president of the 
Presidential Council and secretary general of the Yemeni 
Socialist Party Central Committee, proceeded on an inspection 
tour of military units this morning in the eastern area, during 
which he met military and political leaders. The military 
forces of unity and democracy there are conducting decisive 
military confrontations with the forces of the separatist gang 
of the al-Ahmar clan. 
  A responsible source at the political bureau has told the 
Yemeni news agency, SABA', that brother 'Ali Salim al-Bid made 
the tour in implementation of the resolution adopted by the 
political bureau that party members and leaders should tour the 
various axes following 'Ali 'Abdallah Salih's rejection of all 
the national, Arab, and international initiatives and appeals to 
stop the bloody war he declared against the Yemeni people. 
Salih is targeting the southern and eastern governorates, 
thereby causing the destruction of towns, villages, and 
installations, violating homes and causing the deaths of 
citizens in the areas his forces have entered. This leaves the 
forces of unity and democracy with no alternative but to 
confront those forces, which have transformed unity into a 
bloody struggle. Full historic responsibility is borne by 'Ali 
'Abdallah Salih for this disaster being suffered by Yemen and 
its sons. It was he who during these blessed days decided to 
transform the joy of the sons of the Yemen attending the blessed 
id al-Adha and the fourth anniversary of unity on 22 May into 
days of grief. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

