<F P=100> ISRAEL </F>
<H3> <TI>   Aloni Terms 'Arafat Call for Jihad `Ludicrous' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Aloni Terms 'Arafat Call for Jihad `Ludicrous' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA1805060994 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 0500 GMT 18 
May 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA1805060994 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Minister Shulamit Aloni says 'Arafat's call for 
jihad against Israel is ludicrous. In her opinion, his remarks 
are an extravaganza stemming from profound frustration at having 
achieved less than he had wanted, or perhaps from a dread of 
coping with reality while living in fantasy. 
  Interviewed by a Qol Yisra'el correspondent this morning, 
Minister Aloni said the peace process would continue, and even 
'Arafat would not be able to jeopardize it, because the 
Palestinian people want peace. If he continues daydreaming and 
does not withdraw his remarks, Israel may take time out and 
possibly pursue negotiations with other members of the 
Palestinian leadership -- serious, level-headed people 
representing the Palestinian people, with whom we have become 
acquainted in the course of the negotiations. 

</TEXT>

