<F P=100> ISRAEL </F>
<H3> <TI>   Rabinovich: Syrian Replies `Not Satisfactory' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Rabinovich: Syrian Replies `Not Satisfactory' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA1705201294 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 2000 GMT 17 
May 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA1705201294 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] U.S. Secretary of State Warren Christopher may 
return to the Middle East in a month. This remark was made by 
Professor Itamar Rabinovich, Israel's ambassador to the United 
States, to our political correspondent Shlomo Raz at the end of 
Christopher talks in Jerusalem. Ambassador Rabinovich noted 
that there is no breakthrough in the talks with the Syrians, and 
described them as a living process. 
  He further said that the clarifications received from the 
Syrians are not satisfactory, but they do contain some positive 
and real aspects. Rabinovich noted that Christopher will be 
leaving for Damascus tomorrow with additional Israeli questions 
regarding the Syrian replies and, according to him, we will know 
where the talks are headed in less than two days. 

</TEXT>

