<H3> <TI>   Demonstrators Protest Government Peace Policy </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Demonstrators Protest Government Peace Policy </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA1805051094 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in English 0400 GMT 18 
May 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA1805051094 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] There were demonstrations last night in the wake of 
the terrorist attack in Hebron and in protest against the 
government's peace policy. In Jerusalem's Paris Square opposite 
the prime minister's residence, five demonstrators were arrested 
by police when they tried to break through barricades. 
  On the Jerusalem-Jericho road, police dispersed 
demonstrators 
from the nearby settlement of Kfar Adumim, home of the Hebron 
attack victims. According to Qol Yisra'el's reporter on the 
scene, the demonstrators not only blocked the highway, but 
violently confronted Arab drivers. 

</TEXT>

