<F P=100> ARAB PENINSULA </F>
<F P=101> Oman </F>
<H3> <TI>   Conveys Salih Message to Sultan </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Conveys Salih Message to Sultan </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN1705104294 Muscat Oman Television Network in Arabic 0900 
GMT 17 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN1705104294 </F>
<F P=104>  Muscat Oman Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] His Majesty Sultan Qabus Bin-Sa'id has received a 
message from His Excellency 'Ali 'Abdallah Salih, chairman of 
the Presidential Council in the sisterly Republic of Yemen. The 
message deals with recent developments in Yemen. His Highness 
Fahd Bin-Mahmud Al Sa'id, deputy prime minister for cabinet 
affairs, received the message during his meeting today with His 
Excellency Muhammad Salim Basindwah, Yemeni foreign minister and 
the Yemeni president's envoy, who is currently on a visit to the 
country. 
  The meeting was attended by His Excellency Yusuf Bin-'Alawi 
Bin-'Abdallah, minister of state for foreign affairs, and His 
Excellency Muhammad 'Umar Ba Sa'd, Yemeni ambassador to the 
sultanate. 
  The talks dealt with the developments in Yemen. The two 
sides also reviewed the intensive efforts and continuous good 
offices extended to resolve these developments. 
  His excellency the Yemeni foreign minister praised the 
sultanate's leading role since the beginning of the crisis and 
the special concern demonstrated by His Majesty Sultan Qabus 
Bin-Sa'id for achieving peace and stability in Yemen. His 
excellency noted with appreciation the honest call made by the 
Government of Oman to end the Yemeni crisis to safeguard the 
achievements and gains of the Yemeni people. 

</TEXT>

