<F P=100> ISRAEL </F>
<H3> <TI>   Sarid Denies 'Arafat Claim of Letter on Jerusalem </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Sarid Denies 'Arafat Claim of Letter on Jerusalem </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA1705105394 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in English 1000 GMT 17 
May 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA1705105394 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Knesset Member Yosi Sarid, who was closely involved 
in the Cairo negotiations, denies that 'Arafat has a secret 
Israeli letter regarding the future of Jerusalem. Sarid said 
that the PLO leader does not hold any document or letter whose 
contents have not been presented to the government, the Knesset, 
or the public at large. 'Arafat had been told only what had 
been agreed upon in the Declaration of Principles and nothing 
more, Sarid said. 

</TEXT>

