<F P=100> Egypt </F>
<H3> <TI>   Musa Calls For `Immediate' Cease-Fire in Yemen </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Musa Calls For `Immediate' Cease-Fire in Yemen </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC1705211694 Cairo Arab Republic of Egypt Radio Network in 
Arabic 2000 GMT 17 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC1705211694 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo Arab Republic of Egypt Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Foreign Minister 'Amr Musa returned to Cairo from 
Brussels this evening after chairing meetings of the 
Egyptian-European Cooperation Council. 
  In his arrival statement, he said the council meeting 
discussed means to enhance cooperation between the two sides and 
that an agreement was reached to start a new phase of 
Egyptian-European (?partnership) in a new framework by taking 
the new situation into consideration. 
  Concerning the situation in Yemen, he said the military 
conflict was a tragic action that would achieve no good and that 
it would not resolve the dispute. He added that efforts to 
handle this situation must continue, and there must be an 
immediate cease-fire, disengagement of forces, and a dialogue to 
deal with this situation in accordance to the Yemeni leaders' 
views. He noted that Egypt is monitoring the situation 
carefully. 

</TEXT>

