<H3> <TI>   Naval Ship Acquired From UK Commissioned </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Naval Ship Acquired From UK Commissioned </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK1505104394 Dhaka Radio Bangladesh Network in English 1530 
GMT 14 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK1505104394 </F>
<F P=104>  Dhaka Radio Bangladesh Network </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The commissioning ceremony of the Bangladesh Naval 
Ship [BNS] Shaheed Ruhul Amin was held at BNS Isa Khan base at 
Chittagong port this morning. Addressing the ceremony, 
President Abdur Rahman Biswas said the government has taken 
initiatives to build up a strong navy for safeguarding 
sovereignty of the country. President Biswas disclosed that a 
plan for setting up a marine research institute and procuring a 
survey vessel is now under active consideration of the 
government. He further said there is possibility of adding more 
imported vessels soon to Bangladesh naval fleet to protect 
marine resources within the maritime boundary of the country. 
Our Chittagong representative says the ship procured from the 
United Kingdom having most modern surveillance equipment will be 
used for safeguarding about 44,000 miles of coastal area and 
maritime boundary of Bangladesh. 

</TEXT>

