<F P=102>   LD1605033294 Algiers Radio Algiers Network in Arabic 2200 
GMT 15 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1605033294 </F>
<F P=104>  Algiers Radio Algiers Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The security services reported on 15 May that an 
armed groups support network was dismantled. A total of 31 
people in the support group were active in the areas of Jijel 
and Mila. 
  The same sources emphasized that this support 
network--composed basically of militants from the dissolved 
Islamic Salvation Front-- were involved in the assassination of 
the head of the executive body of Tassala municipality as well 
of the arson attacks in Tassala and Rouached. 
  Furthermore, the special judicial council of the capital 
Algiers issued on 15 May 18 death sentences--four were passed on 
people present before the court. 
  The sentences were given to members of a group consisting of 
47 members active in Tipaza Province, especially in Kolea, 
Douaouda, and Hadjout. 

</TEXT>

