<H3> <TI>   King Receives Israeli Arabs, Stresses Peace </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    King Receives Israeli Arabs, Stresses Peace </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN1705174894 Amman Radio Jordan Network in Arabic 1500 GMT 
17 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN1705174894 </F>
<F P=104>  Amman Radio Jordan Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] His Majesty King Husayn has said that the sons of 
Palestine would always remain in the heart and that they are 
worthy of appreciation and respect, especially those who adhere 
to their land and remain steadfast on it. We have no ambition, 
aim, or purpose other than the return of right to its people and 
owners on their national soil and the achievement of a 
comprehensive and just peace, which future generations can 
accept, safeguard, and defend in an honorable and secure life. 
  His majesty added: We in Jordan are one family of various 
origins and are cohesive in the homeland of the free people. 
Man is valued by the sacrifices he has offered and will offer 
in the future by confronting the challenges and carrying out the 
national duty. 
  His majesty also stressed that Jerusalem and the holy 
shrines 
would remain in our conscience and that we will continue to work 
so that they will be for us all with God's sovereignty 
prevailing and so that these holy lands become a source of 
enlightenment, as they used to be in the past. 
  His majesty's statements came when he received at the Royal 
Hashemite Court today a delegation from the Arabs of Nazareth, 
Akko, Galilee, the Triangle, and the Negev, who came to Jordan 
to extend condolences to his majesty and the honorable Hashemite 
family on the death of Queen Mother Zayn al-Sharaf, beseeching 
Almighty God to have mercy on her soul, grant her paradise, and 
inspire patience to his majesty and the honorable Hashemite 
family. 

</TEXT>

