<F P=100> LEBANON </F>
<H3> <TI>   Defense Minister Rejects Assimilation of SLA </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Defense Minister Rejects Assimilation of SLA </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC1805102894 Beirut AL-SHIRA' in Arabic 9 May 94 p 10 </F>
<F P=103> NC1805102894 </F>
<F P=104>  Beirut AL-SHIRA' </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] In a statement to AL-SHIRA', National Defense 
Minister Muhsin Dallul reiterated his rejection of a 
Washington-backed Israeli request that Lebanon assimilate the 
so-called South Lebanese Army [SLA] and integrate its elements 
in the Lebanese Army as a condition of the Israeli withdrawal 
from Lebanese territories. 
  The issue is an internal Lebanese affair and no country can 
tell us what we should do, the minister said. Those who dealt 
with Israel cannot be equated with other Lebanese militias that 
were disbanded and assimilated. The former are traitors and 
must stand trial in Lebanese courts, Dallul stated. 

</TEXT>

