<F P=100> SOUTH ASIA </F>
<F P=101> Afghanistan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Kabul Police Stations To Be Reactivated </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kabul Police Stations To Be Reactivated </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1405200794 Kabul Radio Afghanistan Network in Pashto 1530 
GMT 14 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1405200794 </F>
<F P=104>  Kabul Radio Afghanistan Network </F>
<F P=105>  Pashto </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] For the ensuring of law and order in the city of 
Kabul, police stations will be reactivated within the security 
zones of Kabul police. This point was expressed by Lieutenant 
General Qara Beg Ezedyar, acting minister of internal affairs, 
to the BAKHTAR INFORMATION AGENCY and he added: Because under 
the provisions of law, police duties are to ensure law and 
order, the leadership of the Ministry of Internal Affairs 
recently decided to replace the officials who have failed to 
discharge their duties in a merited way with faithful and 
professional people to restore law and order very soon in Kabul. 
  With the reactivation of police stations, all irresponsible 
armed men will be expelled from the city. For this purpose, the 
commission of the heads of the Ministry of Internal Affairs 
departments has been assigned to assess the work and activities 
of security officials every day in Kabul, and to make due 
decision for the alleviation of people's problems. Similarly, 
henceforward uniformed police officials will be installed in 
Kabul and the movement of irresponsible armed men will be 
prevented. On top of this, the Ministry of Internal Affairs 
have worked out such serious plans, that with its implementation 
law and order situation will further be strengthened. 

</TEXT>

