<F P=100> Iran </F>
<H3> <TI>   Reaction to Canceled Hajj Rally Reported </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Reaction to Canceled Hajj Rally Reported </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Foreign Ministry Condemns Saudis </H4>

<F P=102> LD1705171794 Tehran IRIB Television First Program Network in 
Persian 1630 GMT 17 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1705171794 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran IRIB Television First Program Network </F>
<F P=105>  Persian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] A Foreign Ministry spokesman has termed the Saudi 
authorities' prevention of the performance of the Disavowal of 
Polytheists ceremony as breach of promise and condemned it. 
  Referring to the Oman agreement between the foreign 
ministers 
of the Islamic Republic of Iran and Saudi Arabia concerning the 
marking of the Day of the Disavowal of Polytheists, the Foreign 
Ministry spokesman said: Not only is disregarding that 
agreement breaking a promise by the Saudi authorities; 
preventing the Disavowal of Polytheists, while Muslims are being 
subjected to oppression and injustice by infidels and 
polytheists, has no political-ideological justification either. 
  Expressing deep regret about the preventive measures of the 
Saudi authorities, the Foreign Ministry spokesman said such 
actions are like raising objections and imposing restrictions on 
the freedom of action of pilgrims of the House of God to perform 
the political-ideological hajj rituals and an effort to render 
the Abrahamite hajj meaningless. 

</TEXT>

