BFN 

  [Text] President Hashemi-Rafsanjani today received Mr. 
Vasim Jaffery, the Pakistani minister of state for economic 
affairs [name and title as heard] and head of the two countries' 
joint committee. 
  At the meeting, the president emphasized the expansion of 
economic cooperation between the two countries in line with 
diplomatic ties. He said: Although there are grounds for 
cooperation between Asian countries, it is not at the expected 
level. Perhaps the tendency to cooperate with the West and lack 
of complete confidence and trust in the natural facilities and 
potentials in the region is one of the factors preventing its 
realization. 
  Mr. Hashemi-Rafsanjani stressed the necessity for the two 
countries' joint committee to become more active to present to 
the world a suitable example of regional cooperation. 
  At the meeting, Jaffery said: Implementing the agreements 
reached between Iran and Pakistan, particularly those reached 
during Mrs. Benazir Bhutto's visit, are always stressed by the 
Pakistani Government. 

