<H3> <TI>   Ministry Condemns Austrian Award for Rushdie </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Ministry Condemns Austrian Award for Rushdie </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1605204894 Tehran IRNA in English 2022 GMT 16 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1605204894 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran IRNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tehran, May 16, IRNA -- Foreign Ministry spokesman 
Mahmoud Mohammadi Monday condemned the Austrian Government's 
granting of an award to sentenced apostate Salman Rushdie and 
interpreted it as background for more disrespect to divine 
religions. 
  The Austrian minister of education and arts recently gave an 
award to the writer of the highly sacrilegious book `The Satanic 
Verses'. 
  The Iranian official said this measure is condemned not only 
by the Islamic republic but also by all world Muslims and 
followers of other divine religions. 
  Rushdie sentenced to death for his crime is in hiding in 
Britain since 1989 with world Muslims determined to bring him to 
justice. 
  The apostate who has hurt the feelings of the world's over 
one billion Muslims, is being backed by certain Western 
countries who from time to time reward him for his misdeed, in 
scant respect of Muslim sentiments. 

</TEXT>

