<H3> <TI>   Oil Minister Explores Cooperation With Kazakhstan </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Oil Minister Explores Cooperation With Kazakhstan </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1505130494 Tehran IRNA in English 1250 GMT 15 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1505130494 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran IRNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tehran, May 15, IRNA -- Kazakh Minister of Energy 
and Fuel resources Kadyr Baykenov and Oil Minister Gholam Reza 
Aqazadeh-Kho'i here Sunday discussed in detail construction of 
an lubricant factory in Kazakhstan and laying of pipelines for 
transfer of Kazakh crude oil by Iranian experts. 
  The two sides also favoured long-term cooperation between 
Tehran and Almaty in the economic and oil fields, which, they 
believed, could serve as a "strong" base for flourishment of 
their industry and economy. 
  They also expressed keenness on expansion and deepening of 
bilateral relations and reviewed formerly reached agreements 
between the two countries' officials on bilateral cooperation in 
the areas of oil and natural gas. 
  Baykenov accompanies Kazakh Premier Sergey Tereshchenko in 
his Iran visit. 

</TEXT>

