<H3> <TI>   New Gas Deposits Sufficient for 250 Years </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    New Gas Deposits Sufficient for 250 Years </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1305135094 Tehran IRNA in English 1207 GMT 13 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1305135094 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran IRNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Rasht, Gilan Prov., May 13, IRNA -- President Akbar 
Hashemi-Rafsanjani said here today that the capacity of the 
discovered gas deposits of the country would be enough for 250 
years. 
  Noting that gas is considered as the best fuel for the 
country, the president said piped gas had been supplied to 240 
cities and towns throughout the country, and that all other 
places should indeed be provided with piped gas. 
  Elsewhere the president said Iran is considered as a steel 
exporter today, and predicted that steel production would reach 
five million tons in the current calendar year. 
  Iran is treading the path of self-reliance in many areas 
including aluminium, copper, and petrochemical industries, he 
added. 

</TEXT>

