<F P=100> Iran </F>
<H3> <TI>   Bandar-e Anzali Declared Free Trade Zone </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Bandar-e Anzali Declared Free Trade Zone </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1605170594 Tehran IRNA in English 1627 GMT 16 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1605170594 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran IRNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tehran, May 16, IRNA -- Bandar-e Anzali on the 
Caspian Sea has been declared a free trade zone. 
  The announcement, according to the Persian evening daily 
KAYHAN TODAY, was made by President Akbar Hashemi-Rafsanjani 
last night, after his inspection tour of the port city in Gilan 
Province. 
  The president on Sunday at the end of his four-day visit of 
Gilan, referred to the capabilities of Bandar-e Anzali and 
stated that a bright future awaits the port and the region. 
  Bandar-e Anzali with its extensive facilities is expected to 
serve as a key link in Iran's trade connections with Caspian Sea 
states which include Azerbaijan, Kazakhstan, the Russian 
Federation and Turkmenistan. 
  The announcement brings to five the number of free trade 
zones in Iran. 
  The other four zones are the Qeshm and Kish Islands off the 
southern Iranian coast in the Persian Gulf, Chahbahar port on 
the Gulf of Oman in Sistan-Baluchestan Province and Sirjan in 
the mineral rich interior of Kerman Province in the southeast. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

