<H3> <TI>   Prime Minister Sidqi's Activities Reported </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Prime Minister Sidqi's Activities Reported </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Vows Development of Upper Egypt </H4>

<F P=102> NC1605152494 Cairo Arab Republic of Egypt Radio Network in 
Arabic 1400 GMT 16 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC1605152494 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo Arab Republic of Egypt Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Today Prime Minister 'Atif Sidqi issued statements 
to reporters announcing that there are comprehensive plans to 
develop, economically and socially, the governorates of Upper 
Egypt and to build a number of industrial zones in the new 
cities of these governorates. Dr. 'Atif Sidqi also announced 
that the Investment Authority has begun to act on President 
Husni Mubarak's directives to immediately launch the projects 
that investors will be carrying out without any hindrances. 
These investments amount to 10 million Egyptian pounds. The 
objective of these projects is to encourage industrial and 
agricultural development, to create new job opportunities, and 
to increase exports. 
  Dr. Sidqi concluded his statements by saying that this was 
one of the major points in President Mubarak's Labor Day speech. 

</TEXT>

