<H3> <TI>   Prime Minister Sidqi's Activities Reported </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Prime Minister Sidqi's Activities Reported </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Receives PRC Delegation </H4>

<F P=102> NC1705173394 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1345 GMT 17 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC1705173394 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 17 May (MENA)--At his office today Prime 
Minister Dr. 'Atif Sidqi received a Communist Party of China 
[CPC] delegation that is visiting Cairo. The delegation is led 
by CPC Politburo member Wei Jianxing. 
  Dr. Sidqi said after the meeting that they had reviewed the 
prospects of further cooperation between the two countries in 
light of the results of President Husni Mubarak's recent visit 
to China. 
  He added that they discussed initial plans for building free 
industrial zones in Sinai, as agreed upon during Mubarak's visit 
to Beijing. Sidqi explained that they also discussed exchanges 
of expertise in the technical and scientific spheres and in the 
field of economic reform. He pointed out that China has 
achieved approximately a 13 percent a year economic growth rate. 
  Ambassador Ahmad Namiq, political adviser at the Prime 
Minister's Office and former ambassador to China, also attended 
the meeting. 

</TEXT>

