<H3> <TI>   Prime Minister Sidqi's Activities Reported </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Prime Minister Sidqi's Activities Reported </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Hails Economic Successes </H4>

<F P=102> NC1705204294 Cairo Arab Republic of Egypt Radio Network in 
Arabic 2000 GMT 17 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC1705204294 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo Arab Republic of Egypt Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] This evening, Prime Minister Dr. 'Atif Sidqi chaired 
a Ministerial Economic Group meeting to review the 
implementation of the economic reform program's second phase and 
to discuss future cooperation between Egypt, the IMF, and the 
World Bank. 
  In a press statement released today, the prime minister said 
that Egypt has achieved distinct success in implementing 
economic reform programs. This, he added, was evident in the 
Egyptian pounds' steady exchange rates against foreign 
currencies, especially the dollar. He said the Egyptian Central 
Bank had a $16 billion surplus and this recently increased by 
$400 million. 
  Sidqi said the government is in the process of devising a 
new 
workers' law to be submitted to the People's Assembly during its 
current session. 

</TEXT>

