<H3> <TI>   Rebel Faction To Participate in 2d Session of Talks </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Rebel Faction To Participate in 2d Session of Talks </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   EA1705220594 Khartoum SUNA in French 1630 GMT 17 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> EA1705220594 </F>
<F P=104>  Khartoum SUNA </F>
<F P=105>  French </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Khartoum, 17 May (SUNA) -- The four-party 
Intergovernmental Authority on Drought and Development 
commission, charged with supervising peace talks between the 
Sudanese Government and rebel factions of southern Sudan, told 
the Sudanese Government delegation, which is currently in 
Nairobi, that John Garang's faction would arrive in the Kenyan 
capital later on 17 May to take part in the second session of 
peace negotiations. This was announced by Mr. Mathiang Malwal, 
director of the Peace Department at the Sudanese Foreign 
Ministry. The Sudanese official, who spoke on the telephone 
with Dr. 'Ali al-Hajj Muhammad, spokesman for the Sudanese 
Government delegation, added that the other faction led by Riak 
Machar was expected to arrive in Nairobi on 18 May from Cyprus, 
where his delegation took part in a symposium on minorities. 

</TEXT>

