<H3> <TI>   Deputy Foreign Minister Views Ties With Iran </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Deputy Foreign Minister Views Ties With Iran </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1805100594 Tehran IRNA in English 0853 GMT 18 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1805100594 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran IRNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Khartoum, May 18, IRNA -- The Sudani deputy foreign 
minister, 'Umar Yusif Baridu, Tuesday called for strengthening 
of ties with Iran and said Khartoum is proud of having relations 
with Tehran. In a meeting with Iranian ambassador to Khartoum 
Majid Kamal, Baridu voiced his country's readiness to promote 
bilateral ties with Iran. He termed his recent trip to Iran and 
his negotiations with Iranian officials as fruitful. 
  Meanwhile, the Sudanese official expressed regret over 
fierce 
fighting in Yemen and Afghanistan. Referring to the 
conspiracies masterminded by the world arrogance against 
Muslims, Baridu urged for an end to the ongoing genocide of 
Muslims and called for the settlement of their disputes through 
peaceful means. At the end of the meeting he welcomed the 
imminent trip of his Iranian counterpart 'Abbas Maleki to Sudan. 

