  [Excerpt] Juba, 15 May (SUNA) -- The convention of Juba 
peace gathering affirms the southerners' extreme desire for 
peace, said Vice President Major General George Kongor. 
  Addressing the opening session of the gathering, Kongor said 
that the gathering is a message unanimously reached by the 
internal front to condemn the acts of those who back the 
continuation of the war in the south. The revolution, he said, 
