<F P=101> Arab-Israeli Talks </F>
<H3> <TI>   'Arafat Clarifies Remarks on `Jihad' in Norway </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    'Arafat Clarifies Remarks on `Jihad' in Norway </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Peres Arrives, Awaits Clarification </H4>

<F P=102> TA1805142394 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 1400 GMT 18 
May 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA1805142394 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] In Oslo today, PLO Chairman Yasir 'Arafat said that 
he is committed to the Document of Principles [DOP] signed with 
Israel, and that he opposes violence and terror. He further 
claimed that his remarks were taken out of context, saying that 
when speaking about jihad, he meant a religious, nonviolent 
struggle and that his remarks were misconstrued in Israel. 
  Our political correspondent Shlomo Raz was told that upon 
his 
arrival in Oslo, Foreign Minister Shim'on Peres announced that 
he would boycott all the events he was scheduled to attend with 
'Arafat until the PLO head personally announced his commitment 
to the DOP and declared his opposition to violence and terror, 
and declared his support for peace. 
  It has just been reported that Minister Peres indeed 
boycotted a luncheon with former U.S. President Carter and PLO 
Chairman 'Arafat. Before holding the joint news conference in 
which 'Arafat made the above announcement, Peres consulted Prime 
Minister Rabin regarding the steps he should take during his 
stopover in Stockholm. [sentence as heard] 

</TEXT>

