<F P=100> INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Arab-Israeli Talks </F>
<H3> <TI>   Peres, 'Arafat Agree on Agenda for Expanded Talks </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Peres, 'Arafat Agree on Agenda for Expanded Talks </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA1905043194 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in English 0400 GMT 19 
May 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA1905043194 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] In their meeting last night in Oslo, Foreign 
Minister Shim'on Peres and PLO Chairman 'Arafat agreed on 
principles and an agenda to begin negotiations on widening the 
authority of Palestinian self-rule to other areas of Judaea and 
Samaria, aside from Jericho. The negotiations are to take place 
in Cairo, but no date was set. Peres told reporters the 
withdrawal from Jericho and the Gaza Strip has been completed 
properly. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

