<H3> <TI>   Syria Said To Propose 4-Year Withdrawal From Golan </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Syria Said To Propose 4-Year Withdrawal From Golan </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA1805165494 Jerusalem Israel Television Channel 1 Network 
in Arabic 1600 GMT 18 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA1805165494 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Israel Television Channel 1 Network 
in Arabic 1600 GMT 18 May 94 </F>

<F P=105> Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Political sources in Jerusalem have said that in 
evaluating the proposals relayed by Syria to Israel through U.S. 
Secretary of State Warren Christopher, one can deduce that 
Damascus is ready to discuss the time factor for a settlement on 
the Golan provided Israel announces its agreement to withdraw 
completely from the Golan. Our political affairs correspondent 
Shlomo Ganor has learned that Syria proposed that the withdrawal 
be carried out within a period not to exceed four years on 
condition that it includes security arrangements on both sides 
of the border. 

</TEXT>

