<H3> <TI>   Delegation of Civilian Policemen Cross Into Gaza </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Delegation of Civilian Policemen Cross Into Gaza </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC1805142994 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1300 GMT 18 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC1805142994 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Rafah, 18 May (MENA)--A delegation of Palestinian 
civilian policemen specializing in traffic, investigation, 
passport, and police station work crossed Rafah border point 
today into Gaza. Another group that is trained to protect 
individuals and vital installations, perform basic security 
operations, and guard civilian administrations, ports, borders, 
and service departments also crossed Rafah border point today. 
They were led by Brigadier Generals 'Abd-al-Hayy Muhammad 
'Abd-al-Wahid and Musa 'Arafat. The two groups, totalling 530 
people, are from the 'Ayn Jalut and maritime police forces and 
had received training in Egypt. 

</TEXT>

