<F P=100> Palestinian Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   General Named Security Head in Gaza Strip, W. Bank </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    General Named Security Head in Gaza Strip, W. Bank </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA1705165694 Tel Aviv HA'ARETZ in Hebrew 17 May 94 p A5 </F>
<F P=103> TA1705165694 </F>
<F P=104>  Tel Aviv HA'ARETZ </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Eytan Rabin] </F>
  [Text] PLO Chairman Yasir 'Arafat decided not to appoint 
Muhammad Dahlan and Jibril al-Rujub as heads of security in the 
Gaza Strip and the West Bank. 
  The HA'ARETZ correspondent has learned from sources in Tunis 
that 'Arafat decided to appoint General Misbah Saqr, an 
inhabitant of al-Shaja'iyah in the Gaza Strip, as head of the 
security services in the West Bank and the Gaza Strip. 
  According to Palestinian sources, 'Arafat chose Saqr, a 
close 
confidant, as Dahlan's and al-Rujub's superior because of their 
close ties with Israeli security elements. Dahlan and al-Rujub 
are due in the territories today. 

</TEXT>

