<H3> <TI>   Fatah Revolutionary Council Holds Ordinary Session </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Fatah Revolutionary Council Holds Ordinary Session </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1805194994 Algiers Voice of Palestine in Arabic 1702 GMT 
18 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1805194994 </F>
<F P=104>  Algiers Voice of Palestine </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] The revolutionary council of the Palestinian 
National Liberation Movement, Fatah, held its 12th ordinary 
session in Tunis. It was the martyr-leader Abu al-Mundhir and 
the Khalil al-Rahman martyrs' session held in the period between 
16 and 17 May. The council heard the report of the central 
committee, read out by brother Abu al-Lutf, as well as the 
reports of the committees related to various activities. 
  Brother President Yasir 'Arafat spoke in detail about what 
happened from Madrid to Cairo, and what has been realized, the 
entry of the Palestinian security forces to the homeland and the 
popular welcome accorded to these forces, as well as about the 
need for the solidarity of all to care for the newly-born 
Palestinian Authority which needs the arms of all cadres and 
leaderships. 'Arafat spoke also about the importance of the 
historic step achieved as a result of the sacrifice of thousands 
of martyrs, injured, prisoners, and detainees. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

