<F P=100> Palestinian Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Hamas Hopes Police Force Not To Be `Burden' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Hamas Hopes Police Force Not To Be `Burden' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN1805182794 Damascus Syrian Arab Republic Radio Network in 
Arabic 1515 GMT 18 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN1805182794 </F>
<F P=104>  Damascus Syrian Arab Republic Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Within reactions to the Gaza-Jericho agreement, the 
Islamic [Resistance] Movement, Hamas, said that the agreement 
and the resulting sell-out and dissipation of Palestinian rights 
has exceeded all limits. In a statement today, the Movement 
voiced its strong rejection of the agreement's provisions and 
all its repercussions on the Palestinians. It said the 
agreement is expected to have serious connotations and 
repercussions which might result in confrontations among the 
Palestinian people themselves, something which the Israelis had 
been endeavoring to realize for a long time. 
  The Movement said: We are apprehensive that when the 
Palestinian police arrive in the Gaza and Jericho areas, they 
will be transformed into forces whose aim would be to continue 
arrests among our people instead of providing security, 
reassurance, and stability which were denied the Palestinian 
people for a long time. 
  The Movement hoped that the Palestinian police force will 
back their Palestinian brothers and will not be a burden to 
them. It warned that the Movement will not sit idly by if these 
forces adopt the role of an honest guard to the Zionist settler 
presence. 
  The Movement said that if the 'Arafat leadership followed 
the 
policy of gagging people, confiscating their liberties, and 
imposing emergency regulations on the citizens, it will enter 
into a big labyrinth and the situation will become like a powder 
keg, liable to explode at any moment. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

