<F P=100> Palestinian Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   PFLP, DFLP Accuse Israel of Pressuring Detainees </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    PFLP, DFLP Accuse Israel of Pressuring Detainees </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN1305200694 Damascus Syrian Arab Republic Radio Network in 
Arabic 1515 GMT 13 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN1305200694 </F>
<F P=104>  Damascus Syrian Arab Republic Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] A media spokesman for the unified Central Command 
of the Popular Front for the Liberation of Palestine [PFLP] and 
the Democratic Front for the Liberation of Palestine [DFLP] has 
said that intense pressure is being applied on their detainees 
inside the prisons of the Israeli occupation authorities to 
secure their approval of the Gaza-Jericho accord. 
  The spokesman said in Damascus today that Israeli 
authorities 
have been seeking to strike a demeaning and cheap bargain with 
the detainees requiring them to undertake in writing that they 
support the Gaza-Jericho accord. 
  The detainees, noted the spokesman, rejected the deal that 
seeks to deprive them of their legitimate right to pursue the 
fight against occupation and settlement activity. He urged 
human rights organizations to move to obtain freedom for the 
detainees and guarantee their right to free self-expression. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

