<F P=100> ARAB AFRICA </F>
<F P=101> Algeria </F>
<H3> <TI>   Zeroual Issues Pardon for `About 1,000' Prisoners </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Zeroual Issues Pardon for `About 1,000' Prisoners </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1905102194 Algiers Radio Algiers Network in Arabic 1000 
GMT 19 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1905102194 </F>
<F P=104>  Algiers Radio Algiers Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] President of the Republic Liamine Zeroual has issued 
a legal decree based on the recommendation of the justice 
minister stipulating the pardon of prisoners who were involved 
in cases not related to crimes of terrorism, sabotage, and state 
security. 
  The decree stipulates the cancellation of the prison 
sentences for those who were sentenced to three months' 
imprisonment, which allows the release of about 1,000 prisners. 
It also stipulates the partial reduction of prison sentences 
ranging between 4 and 7 months. 

</TEXT>

