<F P=102>   NC1805213094 Cairo MENA in Arabic 2040 GMT 18 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC1805213094 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 18 May (MENA)--The central Cairo prosecution 
today started interrogation of 10 lawyers who were arrested 
early this morning for taking part in the events surrounding the 
march they were planning to hold yesterday, Tuesday. 
  Among the 10 lawyers, three are members of the Lawyers' 
Union 
council. These are Mukhtar Nuh, Khalid Badawi, and Jalal Sa'd. 
  The central Cairo prosecution had ordered that 39 
people--among them 25 lawyers--be imprisoned for 15 days for 
interrogation. 
  All those who were arrested have been interrogated about the 
crimes they are charged with, such as participating in criminal 
collusion to incite a riot, demonstrate, or organize protests in 
order to disrupt security and attack some police officers. 

</TEXT>

