<F P=100> Egypt </F>
<H3> <TI>   AL-AHRAM Warns of Middle East `Arms Race' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    AL-AHRAM Warns of Middle East `Arms Race' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC1905064694 Cairo MENA in Arabic 0615 GMT 19 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC1905064694 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 19 May (MENA)--The newspaper AL-AHRAM says 
Israel and the United States have taken practical steps to 
implement the F-15E Eagle aircraft deal. The first batch of the 
advanced aircraft will de delivered to Israel in 1997. The 
newspaper notes that these fighter planes will enable Israel to 
reach distant targets, including Iraq and Iran. 
  In its comment today, AL-AHRAM says this deal has added 
another dimension to the arms race in the region. It has also 
provided further proof that Israel and the United States want to 
maintain their military superiority over the Arabs. In 
addition, Israel will use this superiority as a bargaining chip 
in any settlement with the Arab countries. 
  AL-AHRAM warns that Israel's desire to strengthen its 
military arsenal might harm the peace process because the other 
states might find themselves compelled to increase their 
armament capabilities to achieve a military balance with Israel. 
All this will lead to an arms race in the region. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

