<F P=100> ISRAEL </F>
<H3> <TI>   New Police `Autonomy District' Approved </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    New Police `Autonomy District' Approved </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA1305105694 Tel Aviv HA'ARETZ in Hebrew 13 May 94 p A4 </F>
<F P=103> TA1305105694 </F>
<F P=104>  Tel Aviv HA'ARETZ </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Re'uven Shapira] </F>
  [Excerpts] Prime Minister Yitzhaq Rabin has approved in 
principle the establishment of a new police district, which will 
be the sixth, and which will serve as the unified command of the 
police units in the territories. Rabin has thus accepted a plan 
put forth by Police Minister Moshe Shahal. 
  The establishment of the new district means, among other 
things, that some 1,000 policemen and border policemen will be 
drafted to the force. According to the plan, the Israel Police 
and Border Police units will assume responsibility for security 
and order in the territories under the command of the IDF 
[Israel Defense Forces] and will perform many of the tasks 
currently preformed by the Army. 
  The new district will be commanded by a ranking police 
commander and will be called the Autonomy District. It will 
unite the three currently operating subdistricts of Judaea, 
Samaria, and Gaza. [passage omitted] 
  In the framework of the new police deployment in the 
territories, a unit of 300 border policemen will be set up. It 
will perform guard duties on the roads and crossings between the 
areas of the autonomy and Israel. The new unit has begun 
organizing and drafting men. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

