<F P=100> ISRAEL </F>
<H3> <TI>   Police Unit To Secure Gaza-Jericho `Safe Passage' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Police Unit To Secure Gaza-Jericho `Safe Passage' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA1705164794 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 1500 GMT 17 
May 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA1705164794 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Police Commissioner Asaf Hefetz today disclosed 
plans to set up a guard unit to secure the passage from Jericho 
to Gaza. The unit, called Safe Passage, will daily guard one of 
the four roads on which Palestinians will drive from Gaza to 
Jericho. The unit consists of 400 border policemen: two 
companies of policemen will drive along the road, and two other 
companies will serve as reserves and will be based in Qiryat Gat. 
  Our correspondent Aviv Bushinsky reports that Prime Minister 
Yitzhaq Rabin ordered the establishment of this unit to thwart 
terror attacks, arms smuggling, and provocations by Jews against 
Arabs. 

</TEXT>

