<F P=100> ISRAEL </F>
<H3> <TI>   Gaza Settler Moderately Wounded; Nabulus Youth Shot </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Gaza Settler Moderately Wounded; Nabulus Youth Shot </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA1805192494 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 1900 GMT 18 
May 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA1805192494 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] A resident of the settlement of Netzarim in the 
Gaza Strip was moderately wounded this evening when shots were 
fired at his car from a passing vehicle. 
  Our correspondent Nisim Qeynan reports that Netzarim 
residents reacted to the attack by blocking a traffic axis near 
their settlement. They are demanding that the commander of the 
Southern Command meet them and promise that the IDF [Israel 
Defense Forces] will prevent Palestinians from driving on the 
road where the attack took place. 
  An Arab youth was seriously injured in the eye today by a 
rubber bullet fired by soldiers at stonethrowers in the Nabulus 
casbah. Our correspondent Moti Amir reports that the youth was 
evacuated to a hospital in Jerusalem. 

</TEXT>

