<F P=100> ISRAEL </F>
<H3> <TI>   Estonian Defense Minister Pays Visit </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Estonian Defense Minister Pays Visit </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA1305133494 Tel Aviv HA'ARETZ in Hebrew 13 May 94 p A7 </F>
<F P=103> TA1305133494 </F>
<F P=104>  Tel Aviv HA'ARETZ </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by security affairs correspondent Sharon Shade] </F>
  [Excerpts] Estonian Defense Minister Indrek Kannik arrived 
in Israel yesterday for a four-day visit as the guest of Yitzhaq 
Rabin, prime minister and defense minister. The visiting 
minister will visit Israel Aircraft Industries [IAI] factories 
and will be briefed on the IAI's activity in the sphere of 
overhauling planes and drones. Mr. Kannik will meet with the 
prime minister and senior defense establishment officials today. 
He will also visit the Israel Military Industries [IMI] and 
Elbit Computers. [passage omitted] 
  Czech Defense Minister Antonin Baudys will arrive in Israel 
next Thursday for a five-day official visit. Baudys will meet 
with the prime minister and senior defense establishment 
officials and will visit various defense industries. 
  Next month, Israel will participate for the first time in a 
weapons and military technology exhibition in the Czech 
Republic. Israel's exhibit, which is being organized by the 
Defense Ministry's Defense Sales Department, will include IMI 
and REFA'EL [Armament Development Authority] booths. 

</TEXT>

