<H3> <TI>   Cooperation Memo Signed With Czech Republic </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Cooperation Memo Signed With Czech Republic </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA1905085094 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 0700 GMT 19 
May 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA1905085094 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Today, Israel and the Czech Republic signed a 
memorandum on security cooperation. Prime Minister Yitzhaq 
Rabin lauded Czechoslovakia for assisting Israel during the 
Independence War by sending weapons, without which it would have 
been much harder for us to win our independence. Czech Defense 
Minister Antonin Baudys said that the Czechs assisted Israel in 
the past and are seeking Israel's assistance today. Our 
correspondent Karmela Menashe reports that the Czech minister 
began his official visit to Israel today. 

</TEXT>

