<F P=100> JORDAN </F>
<H3> <TI>   Abu-Nuwar Denies Resignation Offer by al-Majali </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Abu-Nuwar Denies Resignation Offer by al-Majali </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PM1705111894 London AL-SHARQ AL-AWSAT in Arabic 16 May 94 p6 </F>
<F P=103> PM1705111894 </F>
<F P=104>  London AL-SHARQ AL-AWSAT </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] Amman, AL-SHARQ AL-AWSAT -- In a statement to 
AL-SHARQ AL-AWSAT, Jordanian Deputy Prime Minister Dr. Ma'n 
Abu-Nuwar has denied that Prime Minister Dr. 'Abd-al-Salam 
al-Majali submitted his resignation to the Jordanian monarch, as 
claimed by some local papers recently. He said that the 
repetition of such rumors is a matter of speculation by some 
people, and that the decision in this connection is up to the 
king. 
  Abu-Nuwar did not rule out the possibility of a cabinet 
reshuffle after 'Id al-Adha, saying that: "The reshuffle is up 
to the prime minister. That is possible if he sees a need for 
it." [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

