<H3> <TI>   Two Missile Frigates Repaired, Returned to Service </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Two Missile Frigates Repaired, Returned to Service </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1705174994 Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network in Persian 1630 GMT 17 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1705174994 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network </F>

<F P=105>  Persian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Two missile frigates have been repaired and today 
joined the naval fleet of the Islamic Republic of Iran. The 
repair work on the frigates Shamshir [sword] and Zubin [javelin] 
was carried out by experts at factories belonging to the First 
Naval Zone of Iran. 
  Also today, a reconditioned hovercraft joined Iran's First 
Naval Zone Armed Forces. To recondition a hovercraft, with less 
than 75 percent of the parts needing repair or replacement, 
would cost 4 million pounds [as heard] or its equivalent of hard 
currency in a Western country such as Britain. 

</TEXT>

