<H3> <TI>   Borujerdi Concludess Visit to Turkey </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Borujerdi Concludess Visit to Turkey </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1805101094 Tehran IRNA in English 0847 GMT 18 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1805101094 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran IRNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Ankara, May 17, IRNA -- Iran's Deputy Foreign 
Minister for Asia-Pacific 'Ala'eddin Borujerdi conveyed 
President Akbar Hashemi-Rafsanjani's message to his Turkish 
counterpart Suleyman Demirel in a meeting here Monday. During 
the meeting the two sides discussed Tehran-Ankara bilateral 
ties, situation in northern Iraq and the forthcoming visit to 
Iran of the Turkish president. 
  As Iraq's neighbors, Iran, Turkey and Syria are holding 
identical views on the preservation of Iraq's territorial 
integrity. Also, in a meeting with Turkish Minister of Foreign 
Affairs Hikmet Cetin, the Iranian official discussed promotion 
of bilateral relations. Borujerdi concluded his one-day visit to 
Turkey and returned home Tuesday night. 

</TEXT>

