<F P=103> LD1805102994 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network </F>

<F P=105>  Persian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The governor of the Central Bank of the Islamic 
Republic of Iran said exchange rates fluctuations are only short 
term. He said: By implementing monetary, foreign exchange, and 
commercial policies the government intends to steer the foreign 
exchange market toward stable exchange rates. 
  Our correspondent reports that Central Bank Governor 'Adeli 
said: Goods importers are the main applicants for foreign 
currency. 
  He referred to the shock prices on international oil markets 
in recent months and its effect in creating an imbalance in the 
country's balance of trade. He said: Using the two levers of 
foreign exchange and foreign trade policies, particularly in the 
import of goods, in the short term, to restore balance to 
foreign payments is unavoidable. 
  He emphasised the beneficial effects of those policies in 
the 
long run to stabilize exchange rates. He said stabilizing the 
exchange rate is the government's strongest action in protecting 
domestic products. 

</TEXT>

