  [Text] More than 30 billion rials has been allocated for 
the purchase of wheat from farmers in the current season. This 
was announced by the deputy agriculture minister for the 
regulation of agricultural produce at a news conference. 
  He said: About 5,350 tonnes of wheat were purchased from 
farmers last year. Over 5,800 tonnes will be purchased, at a 
guaranteed price of 260 rials per kilogram, this year. He 
added: Other produce will also be bought at guaranteed prices. 
  He added: More than $800 million worth of assorted 
agricultural produce was exported last year. By the end of this 
year, more than $850 million worth of agricultural produce will 
be exported. 

