<F P=100> India </F>
<H3> <TI>   Details of Direct Foreign Investment Reported </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Details of Direct Foreign Investment Reported </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK1705054094 Delhi All India Radio Network in English 0245 
GMT 17 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK1705054094 </F>
<F P=104>  Delhi All India Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] About 14,300 crore rupees of direct foreign 
investment has been approved since August 1991. Over 80 
percent of the investment went to priority industries with fuel 
and oil refinery sector accounting for a maximum of 2,395 crore 
rupees, followed by the power sector, food processing, 
metallurgical industries and electrical equipment and 
electronics. The actual inflow of foreign investment including 
NRI [nonresident Indian] investment amounted to 3,406 crore 
rupees. The maximum investment worth 650 crore rupees was from 
the United States followed by Britain and Germany. 

</TEXT>

