<F P=100> SYRIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Arab League Chief Praises al-Asad, Departs </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Arab League Chief Praises al-Asad, Departs </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN1805191694 Damascus Syrian Arab Republic Radio Network in 
Arabic 1515 GMT 18 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN1805191694 </F>
<F P=104>  Damascus Syrian Arab Republic Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] Damascus--Arab League Secretary General Dr. 
'Ismat 'Abd-al-Majid has praised President Hafiz al-Asad's 
patriotic and pan-Arab stands toward Arab causes, his defense of 
Arab legitimate rights, and his adherence to the just and 
comprehensive peace march. In a statement to SANA upon his 
departure to Cairo today, accompanied by the Arab League 
delegation, he said: I have had the honor to meet with President 
Hafiz al-Asad during my visit to Damascus to attend the 26th 
round of the Joint Arab Action Higher Coordination Committee. I 
briefed the president on the positive results of the committee's 
meetings in terms of strengthening cooperation and joint Arab 
action. 
  'Abd-al-Majid said: It was a good opportunity to hear the 
president's directives and opinions on the various Arab issues, 
particularly the Yemeni situation. The meeting was also a good 
opportunity to hear the president's views in this regard and to 
express my appreciation for the president's intensive efforts 
and endeavors in defending legitimate Arab rights and adhering 
to the just and comprehensive peace march in accordance with 
international legitimacy, the UN Security Council resolutions, 
and the land-for- peace principle. 
  Alluding to the results of the Arab League's Higher 
Coordination Committee meetings over which he presided, 
'Abd-al-Majid said: They were fruitful. Recommendations and 
resolutions were reached connected with all issues on the 
agenda. The results were positive and effective in terms of 
strengthening the march of joint Arab action in all domains at 
the present stage. [passage omitted]. 

</TEXT>

