<F P=100> ISRAEL </F>
<H3> <TI>   Rabin: 'Arafat Clarification on Jihad `Far-Fetched' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Rabin: 'Arafat Clarification on Jihad `Far-Fetched' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA1905042794 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in English 0400 GMT 19 
May 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA1905042794 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Prime Minister Yitzhaq Rabin says he does not 
accept the clarifications of PLO Chairman Yasir 'Arafat that he 
was referring to a peaceful jihad during his controversial 
address at a mosque in Johannesburg earlier this month. Rabin 
says 'Arafat's explanation is far-fetched. Rabin says the 
episode is making the process with the Palestinians more 
difficult and will continue to do so in the future. 

</TEXT>

