<H3> <TI>   Ministry Voices `Reservations' About Economic Talks </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Ministry Voices `Reservations' About Economic Talks </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC1805115794 Beirut Radio Lebanon in Arabic 1030 GMT 18 May 
94 </F>

<F P=103> NC1805115794 </F>
<F P=104>  Beirut Radio Lebanon </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Lebanon today received an official invitation to 
participate in the fifth session of the multilateral talks 
Economic Development Working Group, which will meet in Morocco 
from 15 to 16 June. The invitation was conveyed to Foreign 
Ministry Secretary General Zafir al-Hasan by the Moroccan and 
Russian ambassadors. U.S. Charge d'Affaires Vincent Battle did 
not attend the meeting. 
  A diplomatic source at the Bustrus Palace [Foreign Ministry 
premises] said Lebanon has reservations about participating in 
the meeting of any group emanating from the multilateral talks, 
because the bilateral talks have produced no tangible results. 

</TEXT>

