<F P=100> SYRIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Christopher's Damascus Visit Reported, Assessed </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Christopher's Damascus Visit Reported, Assessed </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Christopher Meets With al-Asad </H4>

<F P=102> JN1805154794 Damascus Syrian Arab Republic Radio Network in 
Arabic 1515 GMT 18 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN1805154794 </F>
<F P=104>  Damascus Syrian Arab Republic Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] President Hafiz al-Asad received U.S. Secretary of 
State Warren Christopher in the People's Palace at 1130 today. 
The meeting was attended by Foreign Minister Faruq al-Shar' and 
Dennis Ross, the U.S. Middle East peace coordinator. 
  Christopher conveyed to the president a message from U.S. 
President Bill Clinton in which he emphasizes the U.S. desire to 
continue its efforts to realize substantive progress in the 
peace process. 
  President Hafiz al-Asad expressed his appreciation for the 
U.S. efforts and stressed Syria's desire to continue the peace 
process to realize a just and comprehensive solution for the 
Arab-Israeli dispute in accordance with international 
resolutions and the land-for-peace principle. Mr. Christopher 
briefed the president on the results of his talks in Israel 
which demonstrated that the differences are wide and great 
because of the large distance between the Israeli stand and the 
pillars of peace which were established at the Madrid 
conference. In this regard, the president reaffirmed Syria's 
stand and its adherence to the bases of the peace process based 
on UN Security Council resolutions which commit Israel to full 
withdrawal to the 4 June 1967 borders in order to realize just 
and comprehensive peace in the region. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

