<H3> <TI>   BBC Correspondent Cited on Fall of al-'Anad Base </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    BBC Correspondent Cited on Fall of al-'Anad Base </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN1905054994 Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network in Arabic 
0430 GMT 19 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN1905054994 </F>
<F P=104>  Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] A number of foreign correspondents yesterday 
visited al-'Anad Base and viewed the fortifications and military 
equipment and vehicles captured by the forces of Constitutional 
legitimacy when they took control of the base the day before 
yesterday. 
  BBC radio correspondent (Simon Angerma), who visited the 
base, said in a report aired by the radio today that he saw some 
tanks of the forces of legitimacy deployed within the perimeter 
of the base. He also noted that the antiaircraft guns repulsed 
several air raids launched by aircraft of the forces of apostasy 
and secession over the area and forced them to flee. 
  The BBC correspondent added that a large number of the rebel 
troops withdrew from the base. He also said he saw the wreckage 
of a helicopter downed near the base entrance and the charred 
corpses of the two pilots. 

</TEXT>

