<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Statement issued by the Ministry of Defense in Sanaa; date </F>
not given] 
  [Text] With the help of almighty God, with the bravery of 
the heroes of the Armed Forces, and with the cohesion of all the 
sons of the people with them, the forces protecting unity and 
Constitutional legitimacy are continuing to carry out their 
combat duties against the gangs of the forces of renegade, 
rebellion, and secession in the Yemeni Socialist Party. Their 
wrong actions surround them and, therefore, they must be 
defeated and must bow to the people's will and their strike 
force on all axes and sectors. 
  On the Abyan-Aden axis, fighting is continuing in several 
directions, and the forces of renegade and secession are trying 
to send innocent people to certain death to merely gain time, 
show empty arrogance, and entertain themselves with destruction, 
after the units of the Armed Forces--the forces of unity and 
Constitutional legitimacy--tightened the siege and closed all 
outlets, and continue to pursue their targets with patience and 
accuracy, taking into account the circumstances in the fields of 
confrontation on this axis. All the feverish air and naval 
attacks have failed. The forces of apostasy and secession 
sustained heavy losses as a result of the lack of control of the 
collapsing and domineering forces that can think only of their 
dark and ominous fate. The brave men in the air defenses 
confronted the aircraft of the forces of apostasy and secession, 
downing two aircraft. The hostile air attacks did not cause any 
losses. 
  On the Shabwah axis, the heroes in the units of the Armed 
Forces are continuing to carry out the duties assigned to them, 
and they made great progress in carrying out their missions 
after they managed to control the Nisab District as a result of 
the great cooperation by the brother citizens, who rushed to 
shoulder their responsibility along with their forces--the 
forces of unity and Constitutional legitimacy. The Armed Forces 
have warmly welcomed a complete battalion of the Hunayshan 
Brigade, as well as the members of the police force in the Nisab 
District, with all their weapons and military hardware. They 
declared they were joining the forces of unity and 
constitutional legitimnacy, rejected the conspiracy of secession 
and the plan of renegade and rebellion, and condemned the sinful 
secessionist elements for what they did to the people, the 
homeland, and the Armed Forces and security. 
  On the al-'Anad-al-Hawtah axis, the heroes in our Armed 
Forces are continuing their progress to carry out the remaining 
combat duties on that axis. In this sector, 22 Katyusha bases 
were seized. The brave heroes in the brave Air Force continued 
to carry out the duties assigned to them with success and 
effectiveness. All aircraft returned safely to their bases. 
  With the continued progress of the forces of unity and 
Constitutional legitimacy to confront the remaining forces of 
apostasy and secession, out of concern about people's lives, and 
to avoid the continuation of the fighting, whose result is 
considered as decided in advance in favor of the forces of the 
people, unity, and democracy, we renew our call to all officers, 
noncommissioned officers, and the soldiers who are still under 
the control of the sinful secessionist forces to leave the 
positions of hostility to join unity, the people, and the forces 
of unity and Constitutional legitimacy. This is the place for 
every officer, noncommissioned officer, and soldier in the Armed 
Forces. They will find complete understanding of their 
situation and the circumstances that forced them to be in 
secessionist rebel ranks. They will get all the attention, 
care, and status they deserve under the banner of the glorious 
Republic of Yemen. 
  As for the forces of error and darkness, the forces of 
secession, fragmentation, and destruction, their fate is known 
because the wrath of justice will inevitably reach them. As God 
has said: And say: `Truth has now arrived, and falsehood 
perished: for falsehood is by its nature bound to perish. 
[Koranic verse] 
  [Signed] The Defense Ministry, Sanaa 

</TEXT>

