<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    YSP Reportedly Fires Missile on Ta'izz </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN1905043494 Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network in Arabic 
0335 GMT 19 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN1905043494 </F>
<F P=104>  Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] A military source has explained to the Yemeni News 
Agency, SABA' that in a desperate, hysterical, and cowardly 
attempt the gang of apostasy and secession in the Yemeni 
Socialist Party [YSP] fired a missile on Ta'izz at 2030 
yesterday, targetting defenseless citizens. But God's 
providence ordained that this missile fall on Sadr Mountain. 
  The source said no human losses were sustained, but that 
children, women, and elderly people in the city and the nearby 
villages were scared and there were some cracks in the houses of 
the citizens from the explosion of the missile. 

