<H3> <TI>   Salih Appoints Representative to Arab League </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Salih Appoints Representative to Arab League </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN1805211794 Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network in Arabic 
2000 GMT 18 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN1805211794 </F>
<F P=104>  Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Presidential Decree No. 24, issued by the Presidency in </F>
Sanaa on 18 May] 
  [Text] The chairman of the Presidential Council, 
  Taking cognizance of the Republic of Yemen Constitution and 
law No. 2 of 1991 on the diplomatic and consular corps, and upon 
the recommendation of the foreign minister and after the 
approval of the Council of Ministers and the Presidential 
Council, decrees the following: 
<H5>  Article I </H5>
  Brother Ahmad Muhammad Luqman, will be appointed ambassador 
and a permanent representative of the Republic of Yemen at the 
Arab League. 
<H5>  Article II </H5>
  This decree will be valid as of date of issue and will be 
published in the Official Gazette. 
  Issued at the Presidency in Sanaa on 7 Dhu al-Hijjah, 1414 
of 
the hegira, corresponding to 18 May 1994. 
  [Signed] 'Ali 'Abdallah Salih, chairman of the Presidential 
Council, 
  Muhammad Sa'id al-'Attar, the acting prime minister, 
  Muhammad Salim Basindwah, the foreign minister 

</TEXT>

