<F P=100> ARABIAN PENINSULA </F>
<F P=101> Saudi Arabia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Security Forces Monitor Iran's Hajj Headquarters </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Security Forces Monitor Iran's Hajj Headquarters </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    `Siege' Ends in Mecca </H4>

<F P=102> LD1805205794 Tehran IRNA in English 2037 GMT 18 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1805205794 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran IRNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Holy Mecca, May 19, IRNA -- The siege of the Iranian 
pilgrim headquarters here by the Saudi security forces ended at 
22:00 hours Wednesday [18 May]. 
  A very big column of all types of armoured vehicles had 
covered the area and al-'Aziz street in order to prevent the 
holding of the annual disavowal of polytheists rally by Iranian 
and other pilgrims. 
  Over the past week Saudi police had harrassed the pilgrims 
and visitors to the HQ. 
  The besiege was severely condemned by Iranian and other 
pilgrims, and the Saudi measure has given rise to widespread 
reaction. 
  On Monday night, the leader of the Iranian pilgrims, Hojjat 
ol-Eslam Mohammad Mohammadi Reyshahri announced the cancellation 
of the rally, in order not to give an excuse to the Saudi police 
to once again desecrate the sanctity of the most inviolable 
sanctuary the Holy Ka'ba. 

</TEXT>

