<F P=100> ARABIAN PENINSULA </F>
<F P=101> United Arab Emirates </F>
<H3> <TI>   Receives Phone Call From Salih </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Receives Phone Call From Salih </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN1805062394 Manama WAKH in Arabic 0530 GMT 18 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> JN1805062394 </F>
<F P=104>  Manama WAKH </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Abu Dhabi, 17 May (WAKH) -- His Highness Shaykh 
Zayid Bin-Sultan Al Nuhayyan, president of the United Arab 
Emirates [UAE], received a telephone call from Yemeni President 
'Ali 'Abdallah Salih this evening. 
  The Emirates News Agency said views were exchanged on the 
current developments in Yemen and the bloody fighting between 
brothers. It added that Shaykh Zayid stressed the urgent need 
to stop Yemeni fighting in order to pave the way for the 
continuation of his highness's efforts to reconcile the Yemeni 
brothers' views. 
  The UAE president appealed to the Yemeni president to do his 
best to put an immediate end to fighting and to exercise maximum 
self-restraint in order to spare blood and safeguard the 
people's lives. He said there will be no victor or vanquished 
among the sons of the one country and that the real loser will 
be the Yemeni people, who will suffer from the destruction 
inflicted on them. 
  Shaykh Zayid regretted what is happening as well as the 
Yemeni president's failure to respond to the repeated calls to 
stop the fighting, stressing that what is taking place is a 
disaster for Yemen and the Arab nation. 

</TEXT>

