<F P=100> Palestinian Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Sha'th Arrives on 24-Hour Visit to Gaza Strip </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Sha'th Arrives on 24-Hour Visit to Gaza Strip </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA2005051594 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in English 0400 GMT 20 
May 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA2005051594 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The PLO' chief negotiator, Nabil Sha'th, arrived 
last night in the Gaza Strip for an unannounced visit. An aide 
said Sha'th was making a 24-hour inspection trip. 
  He crossed the border from Egypt, and after a brief stop in 
Khan Yunus, went into conference with Palestinian officials at a 
Gaza sea front hotel. Sha'th said it was his first visit to 
Gaza Strip in 30 years. He is to hold a post on the council 
which is to administer Gaza and Jericho. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

