<F P=100> Palestinian Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Brings Police Funds </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Brings Police Funds </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN2005115994 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Arabic 1050 GMT 20 
May 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN2005115994 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Interview with Dr. Nabil Sha'th, chief of the Palestinian </F>
negotiating delegation, by Sa'id Mu'addi in Gaza on 20 May -- 
recorded] 
  [Text] [Mu'addi] Dr. Nabil Sha'th, first of all many happy 
returns on the 'Id and welcome to Gaza. 
  [Sha'th] I welcome you and wish you, too, many happy 
returns. 
  [Mu'addi] Dr. Nabil, the visit is perhaps a surprise short 
visit to the Gaza Strip? What is the purpose of this visit? 
  [Sha'th] First of all, I have come to see my homeland. This 
is the first time I have entered Palestine since 1964. My last 
visit to Gaza was in 1964. Therefore, this is a chance for me, 
even for a few moments, to see this beloved homeland, Gaza, and 
its skies and land, and these great people in Gaza. That's why 
when the opportunity presented itself to see Gaza, I did not let 
it pass. 
  Brother Abu-'Ammar [Yasir 'Arafat] wanted to reassure 
himself 
about the situation. He gave me some money that is needed by 
the police force in Gaza. Let us say that it is a small present 
so things will begin in the proper perspective and then, God 
willing, all necessary funds will flow when international 
material assistance becomes available. We will also meet with 
the brothers at brother Abu-'Ammar's request to see about, at 
least, the preliminary and necessary needs after the first week 
of our forces' arrival and the establishment of our authority in 
preparation for the arrival of brother Abu-'Ammar and the 
brothers in the command. God willing, I will be with them. 
  [Mu'addi] Dr. Nabil Sha'th, how do you assess the 
implementation on the ground of the agreement between the 
Israeli and Palestinian side? 
  [Sha'th] With all sincerity, I see that matters are 
proceeding far better than in the best of expectations. Of 
course, I believe matters are going this well because our 
Palestinian people, at least here in Gaza and in Jericho, want 
this agreement to succed. There is complete popular cooperation 
with the Palestinian police. They have adopted the police 
force. Let me say that the people, with their generosity and 
sincere national sense have adopted their soldiers and their 
police force. They are doing all they can to enable them carry 
out their duties as easily as possible. I have noticed, too, 
that, in reality, there are no large problems concerning 
coordination between the Palestinian police force and the 
withdrawing Israeli forces. I believe the beginning of work is 
positive on all levels. We hope we will be able to offer the 
necessary support to complete the requirements for success. 
  [Mu'addi] Dr. Nabil, perhaps you do not know, but an 
incident 
took place at Erez junction. Two IDF soldiers were fired on and 
killed. The perpetrators fled into the autonomy area in Gaza. 
  [Sha'th] No doubt, there will be incidents. However, what is 
important is that the will should exist to overcome them and to 
gradually prevent all acts of violence and move toward real 
peace, which our people and the Israeli people undoubtedly need. 
  [Mu'addi] Dr. Nabil Sha'th from Gaza, thank you very much 
and 
many happy returns, and welcome. 
  [Sha'th] Thank you, and through you I send greetings to all 
the sons of our people throughout our beloved Palestine on the 
'Id and to our brothers in the Galilee, the Negev, Yafo, and 
everywhere. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

