<H3> <TI>   Musa Views Talks on `Partnership Agreement' With EU </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Musa Views Talks on `Partnership Agreement' With EU </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC2005102894 Cairo MENA in Arabic 0850 GMT 20 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC2005102894 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 20 May (MENA)--Foreign Minister 'Amr Musa 
said today that Egypt and the EU countries have agreed to hold 
exploratory preliminary talks to enter a partnership agreement. 
  He added that the talks will involve studying a framework 
for 
new relations, especially as such frameworks have been defined 
between the EU and Israel and between the EU and Morocco and 
Tunisia. He noted that the political form of these frameworks 
is the same but their details differ according to each country 
and its interests and circumstances. 
  Musa said the framework will consider developments in Europe 
and the new concept of relations between the Mediterranean 
countries and Europe, between the Middle Eastern countries and 
Europe, and between Egypt and Europe. 

</TEXT>

