<H3> <TI>   Sudan Seizes Egyptian Properties in Khartoum </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Sudan Seizes Egyptian Properties in Khartoum </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC2005054894 Cairo MENA in Arabic 2232 GMT 19 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC2005054894 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Khartoum, 19 May (MENA)--Egyptian Ambassador to 
Sudan Hasan Jad-al-Haq today lodged a strongly worded protest 
with the Sudanese Foreign Ministry following the Sudanese 
authorities' seizure and closure of Egyptian buildings and clubs 
in Khartoum. 
  The Sudanese authorities today seized the Egyptian Club in 
Khartoum and prevented its Sudanese and Egyptian members from 
entering. They also seized clubs and buildings belonging to the 
Egyptian Irrigation Authority in Sudan and the Egyptian military 
attache in Khartoum. 
  The Sudanese authorities gave no reasons for these measures. 
The measures began in December 1992, when the Sudanese 
authorities seized Egyptian education mission schools, the Cairo 
University branch in Khartoum, and the Egyptian Nasir's Club in 
the Sudanese capital. 

</TEXT>

