<H3> <TI>   Political Parties Deny Supporting Lawyers' Protest </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Political Parties Deny Supporting Lawyers' Protest </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC1905212494 Cairo MENA in Arabic 2105 GMT 19 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC1905212494 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 19 May (MENA)--Official sources of Egypt's 
political parties across the political spectrum have denied 
allegations that they have declared their solidarity with the 
Egyptian Lawyers Association in connection with the events of 
the past two days. 
  The sources, speaking for the leaders of the political 
parties, denied issuing a statement attributed to them earlier 
today. The sources said it is really frightening that some 
people can go to such lengths, fabricate statements, and falsely 
attribute actions to political parties that are carrying out 
their roles and performing their responsibilities with total 
freedom within our current system of democracy. 
  Several political party leaders have exposed the facts about 
the "alleged statement". They said that a few lawyers, with 
well-known sympathies and linked to illegal groups, issued this 
statement and attributed it to the political parties. 
  The leaders affirmed that the entire statement is a mere 
calumny that contradicts the facts. 

</TEXT>

