<F P=102>   NC1605165994 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1405 GMT 16 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC1605165994 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 16 May (MENA)--The Swiss Government has 
decided to write off 150 million Swiss francs--230 million 
Egyptian pounds--of Egypt's debts to Switzerland. 
  Dr. Yusuf Butrus-Ghali, minister of state for international 
cooperation, made this statement today after a meeting with Mr. 
Kelin Berger, Swiss minister of state for foreign affairs [name 
and title as received]. 
  Dr. Butrus-Ghali said the terms of the agreement included 
spending the equivalent of this amount on development projects 
to create additional job opportunities, and to develop projects 
that would contribute toward decreasing the burden of economic 
reform on the low-income sector. 

</TEXT>

