<F P=100> Egypt </F>
<H3> <TI>   Consultative Council Approves Development Plan </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Consultative Council Approves Development Plan </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC1705191594 Cairo Arab Republic of Egypt Radio Network in 
Arabic 1730 GMT 17 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC1705191594 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo Arab Republic of Egypt Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Consultative Council, meeting today under the 
chairmanship of Speaker Dr. Mustafa Kamal Hilmi, approved a bill 
on the economic and social development plan for 1994/1995, 
representing the third year of the current five-year plan. 
  The Council then referred the plan to the president. The 
People's Assembly speaker and the prime minister were also 
informed. 
  Dr. Kamal al-Janzuri, deputy prime minister and minister of 
planning, told the Consultative Council that the planned growth 
rate for the 1994/1995 economic and social development plan is 
4.5 percent compared with 3.6 percent in 1993 and 2.5 percent in 
1992. 
  The planning minister pointed out that this year's plan 
involves the expenditure of 7 billion pounds from the country's 
own resources, 1 billion pounds in the form of foreign grants, 
and 3 billion pounds from the National Investment Bank, the last 
figure representing actual savings. 

</TEXT>

