<F P=100> ARABIAN PENINSULA </F>
<F P=101> Yemen </F>
<H3> <TI>   Al-'Attas Denies Fall of al-'Anad Air Base </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Al-'Attas Denies Fall of al-'Anad Air Base </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   EA1905201394 Aden Yemeni Republic Radio Network in English 
1600 GMT 19 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> EA1905201394 </F>
<F P=104>  Aden Yemeni Republic Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] Engineer Haydar Abu-Bakr al-'Attas, the prime 
minister, said that the al-'Anad base is still under the control 
of our Armed Forces and that brutal fighting had taken place in 
the past days and the pro-al-Ahmar gang forces had been turned 
away. He indicated that 'Ali 'Abdallah Salih had plunged a 
large number of people into these bloody battles. Al-Attas was 
talking to the BBC last night. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

