<F P=100> ARABIAN PENINSULA </F>
<F P=101> Yemen </F>
<H3> <TI>   Cabinet Discusses Ministries' Working Plan </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Cabinet Discusses Ministries' Working Plan </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN1905132594 Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network in Arabic 
1200 GMT 19 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN1905132594 </F>
<F P=104>  Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Council of Ministers resumed its meetings today 
under Acting Prime Minister Dr. Muhammad Sa'id al-'Attar. 
  The Council resumed discussion of the detailed working plan 
of all sectors of work and production in the various economic, 
social, administrative, financial, security, and media fields. 
The plan also deals with all the ministries' responsibilities 
of following up all the facilities and institutions supervised 
by them. 
  The Council discussed means to reactivate these ministries' 
work and to tackle all the disorder caused by the gang of 
secession, rebellion, and apostasy in the leadership of the 
Yemeni Socialist Party [YSP] as part of its policy to sabotage 
unity, democracy, and constitutional legitimacy in the country. 
  The Council endorsed all the proposals and tasks assigned to 
all the government quarters in this regard. The Council also 
decreed that the government shall shoulder the additional flight 
insurance in order to secure the return of citizens from abroad 
to the country, particularly the sick, students, and those who 
left the country for work purposes. 
  The Council listened to the foreign minister's report on his 
recent tour of a number of fraternal Arab countries. 

</TEXT>

