<H3> <TI>   Al-Bid Speaks With Other Arab Leaders on Situation </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Al-Bid Speaks With Other Arab Leaders on Situation </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   EA1905194194 Aden Yemeni Republic Radio Network in Arabic 
1500 GMT 19 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> EA1905194194 </F>
<F P=104>  Aden Yemeni Republic Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Brother 'Ali Salim al-Bid, chairman of the 
Presidential Council and secretary general of the Yemeni 
Socialist Party, yesterday evening held telephone conversations 
with his brother, His Majesty King Husayn Bin-Talal, king of the 
Hashemite Kingdom of Jordan; His Excellency Muhammad Husni 
Mubarak, president of Egypt; His Excellency Hafiz al-Asad, 
president of the Syrian Arab Republic; the custodian of the two 
holy places, King Fahd Bin-'Abd-al-'Aziz Al Sa'ud, king of the 
Kingdom of Saudi Arabia; and His Majesty Shaykh Zayid Bin-Sultan 
Al-Nahayyan, president of the UAE. 
  During the telephone conversations, Brother 'Ali Salim 
al-Bid 
briefed his brothers, the kings and Arab heads of state on the 
latest developments affecting the Yemeni arena, as well as 
developments in the fighting and the war, which was imposed on 
our people in the southern and eastern governorates by 'Ali 
'Abdallah Salih and the al-Ahmar family. He also exchanged 
greetings with them on the occasion of the blessed 'Id al-Adha, 
saying he hoped they and their fraternal peoples would achieve 
further progress and prosperity. 

</TEXT>

