Daily Report 
<DATE1>  20 May 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> ISRAEL </F>
<H3> <TI>   Two IDF Soldiers Shot Dead by `Terrorists' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Two IDF Soldiers Shot Dead by `Terrorists' </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Hamas, Islamic Jihad Claim Attack </H4>

<F P=102> TA2005090694 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 0845 GMT 20 
May 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA2005090694 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Two soldiers were killed this morning south of the 
Erez junction when shot by terrorists from a vehicle which left 
the Gaza Strip and returned there following the shooting. The 
fatalities were reservists. One soldier was named as Moshe 
Bukhra of Netanya, while the name of the other fatality has not 
yet been released. 
  The soldiers were deployed with a third soldier at a 
temporary roadblock south of the Erez junction when a Peugeot 
car suddenly appeared from the south and opened fire at them. 
The two soldiers died on the spot while the third managed to 
return fire at the assailants. The vehicle returned to the Gaza 
Strip. No chase was given because there were no additional IDF 
[Israel Defense Forces] soldiers there. 
  The representative of the Palestinian police force in the 
Gaza Strip told AP by telephone that the Palestinian police 
force did not open fire, and said that from the point of view of 
the Palestinian authorities in the Gaza Strip the incident is 
over. 
  Hamas [Islamic Resistance Movement] and the Islamic Jihad 
claim responsibility for the attack. Hamas said in 
announcements made in Gaza mosques that the assailants belonged 
to 'Izz-al-Din al-Qassam. A different announcement made to the 
foreign press in the Gaza Strip said they belonged to the 
Islamic Jihad in the Gaza Strip. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

