<DOCNO> FBIS4-60070 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drnes098_l_94006" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-NES-94-098 </AU>
Daily Report 
<DATE1>  20 May 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> ISRAEL </F>
<H3> <TI>   Two IDF Soldiers Shot Dead by `Terrorists' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Two IDF Soldiers Shot Dead by `Terrorists' </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Beilin Criticizes Palestinian Reaction </H4>

<F P=102> TA2005105494 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in English 1000 GMT 20 
May 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA2005105494 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Deputy Foreign Minister Yosi Beilin says Israel 
cannot countenance a situation in which terrorists escape into 
the autonomous areas after an attack and the Palestinian 
authorities do not take steps to apprehend them. In an 
interview with reporter Jack Katzenell, Beilin said the 
Palestinian administration is still in diapers, but it must 
disarm the Hamas [Islamic Resistance Movement] terrorists. 
Today's terrorists' attacks were both sad and serious, Beilin 
said. 
  [Begin Beilin recording] It is sad because of the people who 
were killed and injured, and it is serious also because of the 
fact that the Palestinians did not react properly to this event. 
What they have to do is to claim responsibility to assure that 
they are doing their utmost in order to disarm those people, and 
to pursue them, and to find them. The difficulties are there, 
we know that, we don't dismiss it, but it is now the duty of the 
Palestinian police to deal with the matter, to find the people, 
and to do whatever possible in order to prevent a recurrence of 
those events in the future. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

