</HEADER>

<F P=100> ISRAEL </F>
<H3> <TI>   Two IDF Soldiers Shot Dead by `Terrorists' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Two IDF Soldiers Shot Dead by `Terrorists' </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Opposition Reacts Sharply to Incidents </H4>

<F P=102> TA2005105794 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in English 1000 GMT 20 
May 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA2005105794 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] The opposition has reacted sharply to the 
attacks in the Gaza Strip. The National Religious Party has 
called on the public to rise up and prevent what it terms the 
government head-long dive into the abyss. The head of Tzomet, 
Refa'el Eytan, says the attacks are the inevitable outcome of a 
government that ordered the IDF [Israel Defense Forces] to flee 
Gaza, in his words, in the middle of the night. 
  The YI'UD [Independent and Democratic Israel] party is 
demanding that the prime minister halt the passage of all 
vehicles from Gaza into Israeli territory. A short time ago, 
reporter Harley Braidman got this reaction from the senior Likud 
member of the Foreign Affairs and Defense Committee Eliyahu 
Ben-Elisar: 
  [Begin Ben-Elisar recording] This is a tragedy because again 
everybody can see what a catastrophe was bestowed upon us by a 
government which is blind and weak, and is pursuing a policy 
which could not succeed, could have no chance of succeeding 
because it is against nature, and against human character and 
mentality. How can a foreign and powerful nation like Israel 
try to strike a peace agreement with a snake, with 'Arafat, with 
the PLO, and believe that this is the only way out of the 
difficulties, and trust such a man, who is not being trusted by 
his Arab colleagues? Believe me, I know what I am saying. 
[passage omitted] [end recording] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

