<F P=100> ISRAEL </F>
<H3> <TI>   Likud, UTJ Submit No-Confidence Motions </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Likud, UTJ Submit No-Confidence Motions </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA1905195594 Jerusalem Israel Television Channel 1 Network 
in Hebrew 1700 GMT 19 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA1905195594 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Israel Television Channel 1 Network 
in Hebrew 1700 GMT 19 May 94 </F>

<F P=105> Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The coalition is recruiting all its members prior 
to the no-confidence motions that will be heard on Monday [23 
May]. The United Torah Jewry [UTJ] has submitted a no-confidence 
motion over the desecration of the Sabbath and holidays during 
the IDF's [Israel Defense Forces] withdrawal from the Gaza 
Strip. The Likud submitted a motion of no confidence because 
because it alleges that the government is prepared to hold 
negotiations over the future of Jerusalem. 

</TEXT>

